title: chili con queso dip #2
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Cube the Velveeta cheese. Use a double boiler or the microwave.
Melt the cheese in the sauteed onions and celery.
Add the can of chopped chili peppers. Add milk slowly until you get it as thin as you like.

title: ham
directions: Fry bacon crisp;
drain on paper towel.
Slice tomatoes thin. Combine the tomatoes and the bacon.
Add salad dressing and sweet pickles.

title: blueberry bread pudding
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside. Combine eggs, milk, sugar and lemon juice in a large bowl; beat well.
Add bread cubes and let stand for 5 minutes.
Fold in blueberries and lemon rind.
Spoon into prepared dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly browned and puffed.
Serve warm with Custard Sauce.

title: mandarin orange or orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, Crisco and orange slices and bake in 3 (9-inch) round layer cake pans at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip, crushed pineapple and juice and package of pudding together and spread between cooled layers, on top and sides.
Keep cake in refrigerator.

title: garlic bread with parmesan cheese
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch (or less) slices.
Mix butter, parsley, oregano and garlic.
Put butter mixture between slices with a fork.
Wrap bottom and sides in long strip of aluminum foil, open at top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and parsley.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water, then add other ingredients, stirring as you add them.
Set in freezer for approximately 8 to 9 hours.
Stir hourly after the first 4 hours.
This recipe makes 1 gallon and 8 gallons serves 150 people.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let come to a boil, then ready to use.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces and arrange as a bed in a large chilled salad bowl or on a platter.
Arrange separate ingredients in wedge-shaped sections on top of lettuce; bring to the table to show off the colorful arrangement.
Add salt, pepper and vinegar and toss lightly.
Add oil and toss again.

title: vanilla pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream sugar and butter together; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry mix beginning with flour, then milk, ending with flour.
Beat well after adding all of flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
In bowl, blend together soup, milk, mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir in cheese, tuna and pimento.
Gently fold in cooked macaroni.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine crumbs, melted butter and paprika; sprinkle atop casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through, 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix and set aside the flour, sugar and Crisco.
Mix and add Karo syrup, boiling water and baking soda to pie crust in thirds.

title: jello dessert
directions: Make Jell-O following directions on box minus 1/2 cup water. Let Jell-O firm slightly and add all ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with vegetable dippers or with tortilla chips (the blue corn type is good).
Can also put dip in hollowed-out loaf of bread and serve with chunks of bread.

title: best jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and beat well. Stir in peppers, onion, sugar and pimento. Grease 9 x 14-inch baking dish. Heat and pour half of batter in it. Sprinkle with half of cheese. Add remaining batter and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: lamb and artichoke stew
directions: In large frying pan, melt butter.
Saute lamb until lightly brown; remove from pan and reserve.
Saute onion, garlic and parsley.
Put meat and everything from the saute pan into a large heavy kettle.
Add salt, pepper, tomato paste and wine.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until lamb is tender.
Add artichokes, dill weed and lemon juice and continue to simmer until all is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8. Nice served over pilaf.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beef until red is out of meat.
Drain all fat from meat. Add other ingredients and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrots with pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Add 3 tablespoons chopped sweet pickles.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add juice.
Add to cream cheese gradually, blending until smooth.
Chill until slightly thickened. Add fruit cocktail.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 1/2-quart greased mold.
Chill
until firm.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased 9-inch casserole.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix
with
a
spoon
in mixing bowl the sugar, eggs and oil. Sift
dry ingredients together.
Gradually add to liquid mixture; mixing well.
Add apples, vanilla and nuts; mix well. Pour	into greased
and
floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven 40	to 60 minutes at 350°.
Do not open oven during first 30 minutes.
A confectioners sugar glaze can be used.

title: corned beef cabbage rolls
directions: Canned corned beef never has enough onion to give it good flavor, so add the onion and mix well.
Divide into 8 portions and shape into oblong rolls.
Separate cabbage leaves from a head by cutting out the core and carefully working the big leaves off. Parboil them in slightly salted water just long enough to wilt slightly, about 2 minutes.
Drain well, but reserve the liquid in which they are cooked.
Roll the corned beef rolls in them, tie with string or secure with toothpicks and arrange close together in a shallow, well-greased casserole.
Dot with butter and add about 1/2 cup of the cabbage liquid.
Bake 20 minutes in a moderate oven, 350°, basting 2 or 3 times.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
This serves 4.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Combine and bring to a boil.
Boil or simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Can.

title: 18 day pickles
directions: Add salt to cucumbers.	Let stand 4 days.
Wash pickles 3 times.
Add
alum
and
fill
with water.
Let stand 1 day. Rinse well.
Pour
vinegar
over pickles.
Let stand 10 days. Drain vinegar and rinse.	Add 3 cups sugar.
Repeat last step for
3 days.
(Total
9 cups sugar.) Store in gallon jug.	No seal necessary.

title: chicken breasts with mustard and cream
directions: Pat chicken dry with paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute chicken in butter and oil in a large skillet until lightly golden, about 6 minutes. Turn.
Lower heat.
Saute until chicken is just tender, about 4 minutes longer.
Chicken should feel springy with no pink remaining.
Cover skillet and cook 2 minutes longer to steam.
Remove to warm platter.
Cover and keep warm.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, leaving peanut butter to last.
Stir until blended in.
Freeze in your electric ice cream maker or hand freezer.

title: chicken italiano
directions: In a large skillet, combine 1/4 of the dressing and chicken and saute until chicken is brown.
Add the vegetables and rest of dressing.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes and serve over the hot pasta.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve hot or cold with Melba crackers.
Also good to stuff a tomato or avocado.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger meat and add mushrooms, onion and spaghetti mix. Mix well.
Layer in casserole dish: sauce, cottage cheese, noodles and cheese; at least 2 layers.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Blend in shortening with pastry blender until like coarse meal.
Combine orange juice, eggs, rind, nuts and cranberries in a large bowl.
Add sifted ingredients to this bowl and mix by hand.
Spoon into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Add blueberries and spread sugar over berries.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and melted butter using two knives or a pastry blender to mix.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Sprinkle over berries.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with desired topping.

title: oven crisped fish
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Oil a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine bread crumbs and next 6 ingredients; set aside.
Rinse fillets; pat dry. Combine lemon juice and wine in shallow pan.
Dip each fillet in lemon mixture, then in seasoned crumbs.
Make certain each piece is well coated.
Place fish in pan.
Drizzle evenly with oil.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Cut into serving size pieces, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat; drain well. Add other ingredients. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes and enjoy.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Crumble sausage in frying pan.
Cook and drain.
Press crescent rolls onto greased pizza pan to make crust.
Place sausage on crust.
Layer hash browns, then cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Let dough rise until doubled in size.
Melt margarine in small saucepan.
On a floured surface, roll dough into a 16 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread 2 tablespoons of melted margarine over the rolled dough.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Generously sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up, starting with 16-inch side.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar, water and corn syrup to remaining margarine. Stir until well mixed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chopped nuts over the top.
Cut rolled dough into 15 pieces.
Arrange evenly over the top of the syrup and nuts. Cover and let rise until light, 5 to 7 hours. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Loose sides with a knife.
Carefully turn pan upside-down over a platter or baking sheet.
(The syrup is very hot!)
Cover loosely with foil until ready to serve.
These are best when eaten fresh and warm.

title: tasty tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well.
Sprinkle cheese evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix strawberries with cornstarch.
Let set and cool.
Blend flour, brown sugar, margarine and nuts and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: california casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and green pepper in shortening.
Add remainder of ingredients, except noodles.
Layer noodles and sauce in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper in skillet.
Stir until crumbly; drain.
Add onion, celery, carrot, green pepper, kidney beans, cabbage, diced tomatoes, tomato soup and tomato juice.
Mix well and bring to boil.
Add beef cubes.
Reduce heat. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: grandma kuntz's cheese cake
directions: Cream Ricotta and cream cheese.
Add sugar, flour and vanilla.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream, mixing well.
Bake in a 10-inch spring-form pan, placing this spring-form pan inside a roasting pan filled with 1 inch of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off; do not open for 1 hour.
Let cool, then refrigerate overnight.
Remove from pan and serve. Excellent!
(Not fat-free.)

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Stir together crumbs, sugar, cocoa and butter.
Press into the bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: chinese bean salad
directions: Combine beans, water chestnuts and onion rings in large bowl. Dissolve sugar in vinegar in pint jar tightly covered.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and shake.
Pour over beans.
Chill overnight.
Serves 8.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Do not use electric mixer.
Drain juice from fruit into cup.
Stir baking powder into juice.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except juice and fruit.
Mix thoroughly; add juice and fruit.
Stir to combine throughout.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 1 hour.
Glaze while hot.

title: magic pan house salad dressing for spinach salad
directions: Whisk together all ingredients.
Chill at least 20 minutes. Whisk again before serving.
Serve over salad of leaf lettuce, spinach, bacon bits, mandarin oranges (drained) and almond slices. Goes well with main dish of crepes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions separately; drain.
Combine pepper and onion pulp.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Add sugar, water, vinegar, salt and dill seed.
Boil gently 5 minutes.
Fill jars and process in boiling water 5 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Roll the meat in all the flour you can get to stick.
Cook in a large pot until gray; stir often, do not brown.
Add 3 quarts water, then add remaining ingredients through the tomato juice, cooking very slowly.
Add the beans and crumbs last.
Simmer in large pot or electric roaster.
May be frozen.
Makes 50 cups.

title: rice crispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large pan over low heat, stirring until melted.
Add marshmallows; stir often over low heat until melted completely.
Take off heat and stir in cereal.
Using a spoon covered with butter, press mixture into a 9 x 13 sprayed pan. Cool.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Using blender at medium speed, blend all ingredients, except 3 strawberries, until smooth.
Cover and chill.
To serve, garnish soup with remaining 3 slices strawberries.
Makes 3 (1 cup) servings.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Mix Italian dressing, brown sugar, butter, onion powder and garlic powder together in a bowl.
Microwave for a few seconds until butter is melted.
Stir well.
Taste and make sure it is sweet enough.
Wrap about 5 or more green beans in a 1/2 slice of bacon.
Place bundles in a glass casserole dish and pour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until bacon is done.
Green beans should be shriveled up on the ends.

title: peach daiquiri
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; pulse until mixture is smooth.
Serve immediately or pour into small freezer bags and freeze.
Thaw partially to slush consistency before serving.

title: fried squash cakes
directions: Mix all together as you would potato cakes and drop by large spoonfuls in hot oil and margarine, mixed.
Fry slowly until golden brown. Turn as cakes brown.
Makes 8 medium cakes.

title: cream of broccoli soup by pat schaub
directions: Boil water, then add salt, pepper, broccoli, celery and onions and cook until tender.
Lower heat to simmer and add margarine, cheese and milk.
Stir cornstarch with a little water and add to thicken just a little.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Saute chicken tenders in oil in frying pan or wok until cooked through.
Add peppers and onions.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add taco seasoning and water.
Cover and simmer until sauce has boiled down to a thick paste.
Serve in tortillas with garnishes.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch or two loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.
Mix all ingredients except cherries; beat 30 seconds.
Stir in cherries. Pour into pan(s).
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 9-inch loaf 65 to 70 minutes and 8-inch loaves 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate no longer than 1 week.

title: gina's breakfast casserole
directions: Unroll rolls and lay flat in baking dish.
Brown sausage and sprinkle over rolls.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs and pour over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: party pizza
directions: Cook meats slowly and drain well.
Stir other ingredients into meat.
Blend well.
Spread on rye bread.
Freeze on cookie sheets. Store in plastic bags.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except apples and pecans.
Beat well, then add apples and pecans.
Bake in loaf or tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
When cake is done, remove from oven.
Leave the cake in the pan and glaze (recipe follows).

title: empanadas(meat patties)
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
In small amount of olive oil, saute green olives, garlic, onion, bell pepper and salt for 5 minutes.
Add beef, tomato sauce and Goya Sazon.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Let cool before stuffing discos.

title: very moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Add vinegar, oil, vanilla and cold water.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool.
Frost with Snow Frosting.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together and alternate in a pan with layers of buttered bread cubes or 3/4 cup crumbs and 1/2 stick oleo.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
You can also just put crumbs on top and bottom.

title: quick punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid in 2-quart pitcher.
Mix all together in punch bowl, enough for one bowl.
Add ice ring; serve.

title: homemade taco seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use instead of 1 (1 1/4 ounce) taco seasoning mix.
If not using the entire amounts, store tightly covered in cool, dry place.

title: quick dessert
directions: Stir all together and keep refrigerated.

title: divinity peanut butter roll candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and
water;
cook	until
a little forms a very hard ball in
cold water or use a candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites until
stiff
and
don't pour syrup over the egg whites until you let
it
cool for a minute, then beat the mixture until very stiff and
pour
out on a board covered with powdered sugar. Roll out
and spread with as much peanut butter as you like.
Roll up and slice.
Store in tin box.

title: fresh vegetable combo
directions: Cook celery
15 minutes and add the rest of the vegetables and cook until tender.	Add salt, pepper or your favorite seasoning.

title: chili
directions: Mix hamburger meat with tomato soup and tomato sauce.
Add onions, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 45 minutes, stirring often.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Mix all together and shape like a cake.

title: beef tips in wine
directions: Saute tips in tad amount of oil.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Put tips in casserole dish and add liquid mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 2 hours or until done.

title: white frosting
directions: Mix together.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Cream together eggs, sugar and butter; add cream corn. Add dry ingredients.
Blend in cheeses last.
Reduce heat to 300°. Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Beat 1 egg and mix with dry cake mix and melted butter.
Pat into an 8 x 12-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix cream cheese and remaining 2 eggs.
Slowly stir in sugar and add coconut and pecans.
Spread over cake.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: inside-out stuffed peppers
directions: In a skillet, brown beef; drain.
Transfer to a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add the next 8 ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.
Uncover and sprinkle with the cheese; return to oven until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: baptist pie
directions: Mix and pour in graham cracker crust; top with Cool Whip.

title: filling
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, cornstarch and milk.
Cook in heavy pan over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick; add vanilla. Cool.
Add nuts, reserving a few for top.
When cool enough to spread, fill and frost cake.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, syrup and oleo, mixing to blend. Do not overbeat.
Stir in rum and pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until filling is golden and firm to light touch.

title: green chili enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; salt and pepper to taste.
In 6-quart pot add soups and water as directed on can.
Add everything else except tortilla chips and cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Use a large deep casserole dish.
Add a layer of chips, a layer of drained meat mixture, a layer of soup mixture and a layer of cheese and repeat until all used.
Put it in the oven at 400° until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: no-bake apricot cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll dough into small balls. Place on waxed paper or foil and refrigerate.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cookies will keep for a few weeks without freezing.

title: praline grahams
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Break crackers in sections and place on foil.
Melt butter, margarine and sugar.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla. Pour evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Peel off foil.
Store in container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine stuffing mix and margarine in bowl.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with half the stuffing mix.
Combine chicken soup, celery soup, Milnot, peas, chicken broth, chicken, celery and onion and pour into casserole; cover with the remaining stuffing mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Saute ground beef, celery and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a hot greased skillet at 400° until done.

title: italian sesame seed cookies
directions: Nana is now 88 years young but unfortunately can no longer bake her wonderful cookies.
She loved to cook.
She always had wonderful cookies waiting for us when we visited.
This is Nana Mancuso's old Italian Sesame Seed Cookie recipe.
These are great with a cup of coffee!

title: quick fudge nut chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
In saucepan, put butter, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture; mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Pour into a 10 x 15-inch greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes, or until done.
While cake is baking, make icing.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in pan. Add rice and brown slightly. Add onion, bell pepper and ground beef. Stir until meat is slightly browned. Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings. Bring to a boil and then simmer on low heat for 25 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Whip the flour and margarine together with mixer.
Add the chopped walnuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375°.

title: cherry crumble cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread cherries in bottom of pan.
Spread pineapple (undrained) on top of cherries.
Put cake mix on top of pineapple.
Put butter on cake mix evenly.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli with honey and mustard sauce
directions: Blanch or steam broccoli.
To make the sauce, mix the water with the mustard, honey and pepper.
Toss sauce with the broccoli florets.
For variation, use other steamed vegetables, such as cauliflower, squash or spinach.

title: party chicken
directions: Cover bottom of 8 x 12-inch greased casserole dish with cut-up chipped beef.
Wrap each breast with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Place on top of chipped beef.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: peppermint candy cookie
directions: You will also need 1 round cookie cutter (3-inch), 24 pieces 12 x 12-inch clear squares cellophane and 1/2-inch holiday ribbon. Preheat oven to 350°. Tint the cookie dough with the green food coloring and flavor it with the peppermint extract. Roll it to 1/4-inch thickness and then press out 24 circles, using the cookie cutter. Bake them for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix eggs, peppers, cream cheese, onion and salt.
Cut tortillas, quartered, and spread with mixture.
Roll and fasten with toothpicks.
Fry in 360° hot fat until brown.
Makes 24 canapes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in a lightly greased iron skillet 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: grilled lobster tails(aragosta coda alla griglia)
directions: Preheat
grill.
Cut
lobster
along
edges
of
tail undershells with scissors.
Clip
off
fins
on
outer
edges. Peel back and discard
soft
undershell.
Bend tail backwards, cracking joints to prevent
curling.
In saucepan mix together butter, garlic, lemon juice, parsley, salt, pepper and chives; saute for 1 to 2
minutes.
Brush
lobster
tails
with butter mixture.
Grease rack and
place lobsters, shell side down, on hot grill.
Cover tail with foil and grill for 5 to 7 minutes. Brush again with butter
sauce
and
turn
lobster.
Cover and cook an additional 3 to 5 minutes, until lobster turns opaque. Serve with remaining sauce.
Garnish
with
lemon
wedges
and serve with drawn butter, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: date and nut cookies
directions: Mix in usual way and drop on cookie sheet (greased).
Bake in moderate oven, 375° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: texas vegetable soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook beef, onion and celery until beef is browned; drain off excess fat.
Add rest of ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 10 minutes. Portion of soup may be removed to freeze for snacks.
Cook remaining soup until carrots are tender, about 15 minutes.
Makes 3 3/4 quarts in all.

title: "mock" seafood salad
directions: Heat jello and tomato soup until dissolved; cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Pour into dish or mold ring.
Note: May use individual cups.
Also you may add crab or shrimp.

title: yuletide apple-pecan pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Place apple slices in bottom of pie.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Combine margarine, granulated sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa and eggs.
Mix well. Add baking powder, salt and flour.
Blend well. Stir in vanilla. Pour batter into slightly greased 9 x 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or longer.

title: frankfurters spanish style
directions: Cook rice in large quantity salted water; drain.
Combine soup and rice in baking dish.
Add dash of thyme.
Split frankfurters; spread with mustard, then insert strips of cheese.
Wrap with bacon.
Place frankfurters on top of rice mixture.
Bake in moderate oven, 375°, for about 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp. Makes 4 generous servings.

title: big d's snack stuff
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large can.
Mix popcorn oil and ranch dressing; pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well and serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls in cookie sheet.
Cook according to directions on package.
Mix cream cheese, dressing and milk in blender.
(Works best if cream cheese is not softened.)
Spread mixture over cooled crescent rolls.
Place vegetables on top.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 2 cookie sheets.

title: peaches 'n cream
directions: Whip heavy cream until peaks form.
Drain can of sliced peaches and fold the peaches into whipped cream.
Spread into metal pan and freeze.
(Tastes like ice cream.)

title: country chicken or squirrel(boil)
directions: You will need a large cooker.

title: country apple pie
directions: Arrange apples in pie shell.
Mix together and pour over apples, the sugar (3/4 cup), flour, salt, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and the whipping cream.
Mix together the 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: In double boiler, melt the cheeses and milk; set aside. Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Combine chili and cheese in double boiler. Serve hot with your favorite chips or crackers. Makes 4 servings. Preparation time: 0:30.

title: cheddar squash casserole
directions: Cook squash slices and onion in boiling water until tender. Drain.
Mix sour cream, egg yolks and flour; fold in egg whites. In a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish, layer 1/2 squash, 1/2 sour cream mix and 1/2 cheese.
Crumble bacon over cheese.
Layer remaining squash, sour cream mix and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure sifted flour.
Add salt, baking powder and soda; sift together.
Cream the butter; slowly add sugars.
Cream until fluffy and light.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour. Beat until smooth.
Mix in oats and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: upside devil's food cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in cake pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped walnuts on top.

title: best-ever stew
directions: Put in casserole.
Cook until meat is tender in about a 325° oven.
If it gets dryish, add more wine.
It is not necessary to flour and brown meat.

title: jay's european chicken
directions: Cut chicken up and place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put bell pepper and onion over chicken along with mushrooms.
Mix seasonings together and sprinkle over that.
Spoon soup (without liquid, straight from can) over top and cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice and a vegetable.

title: delicious plum cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs (one at a time) and plums.
Continue beating about 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
While hot, pour on glaze.

title: beans
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients together.
Add mustard, brown sugar, tomato soup and tomato paste.
Mix all together and cook for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over beans.
(Do not drain any of the beans.)
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit.
Add pudding mix and let stand 10 to 15 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip and chill until ready to serve.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In skillet, put water, margarine, salt and pepper.
Add shredded cabbage and bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and cook, stirring occasionally.
Cook until just tender.
Do not over cook.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, syrup, water and peanuts to a boil.
Cook on medium high, stirring constantly, until hard crack stage (about 300° on a candy thermometer).
Remove from heat, then quickly stir in soda.
Be sure to mix completely.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool completely; break into pieces.

title: perfect standing rib roast
directions: At
least
to 4 hours before serving, place the room temperature
roast,
sprinkled
with
seasonings, in a shallow open pan
(fat
side up), resting on bones or on a rack.
Bake for exactly
minutes in a preheated 375° oven.
Do not add water. Do
not
cover.
Do
not baste.
Turn off oven.
Leave the roast in the oven with the door closed.
Do not open oven. Turn oven on again at 375° for 45 minutes before serving.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Delicious.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground meat, green pepper and onion. Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake just like regular corn bread directions.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix everything together, except pecan halves and vanilla. Pour into pastry-lined pan.
Bake until set, about 40 to 50 minutes, at 375°.

title: sock-it-to-me-cake
directions: Mix together everything, except nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon, and pour half into tube pan.
Mix the brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts together.
Sprinkle over batter, then pour rest of batter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden cheese and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, tomatoes, green pepper, onion and seasonings. Place alternate layers of rice mixture and slices of cheese in a 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great to take to those church or family dinners.
If you like hot peppers, I add some chopped jalapeno peppers with the green peppers.

title: grandmother estelle's osgood pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into pie crust; dot butter on top. Bake at 285° for 50 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Stir in applesauce and dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: thirty day friendship cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs and juice.
Mixture will be thick and stiff.
Fold in the fruit (1 cup per cake).
Add nuts, raisins and coconut.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetarian tagine
directions: Peel and cube all vegetables into 1 inch squares.
Cut onion and garlic into small dices.
Add spices and salt to taste.
Warm oil.
Saute onion and garlic in oil; add vegetables, spices and water.
Turn heat to medium-hot.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Serve with lemons, olives and mushrooms.

title: shasta mountain brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease, then flour two 9 x 9-inch pans. Melt chocolate and butter over low heat; cool.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until thick and smooth, about 3 minutes.
Stir in the chocolate-butter mixture, then slowly add the flour.
Do not overmix.
Fold in the cookie crumbs and most of the pecans. Spread the batter evenly into pans and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake about 40 minutes, or until set.
(Brownies will be soft in the center.)
Let cool completely.
Yields 18 brownies. Enjoy.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot or casserole.
Cook 3 to 4 hours or in a casserole, bake at 325° for 1 hour. Serves a family of 7.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put ingredients in boiler; stir until dissolved.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Amounts depend on quantity of eggs.

title: taco salad
directions: Break up lettuce in small pieces.
Cook ground beef and add onion and taco seasoning mix.
Drain well and cool before adding to lettuce.
Add shredded cheese, drained kidney beans and diced tomatoes to lettuce.

title: fruit salad ole'
directions: Toss salad with Vinaigrette Dressing.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: sheepherder's bread dip
directions: Slice off top of Sheepherder's bread and hollow out (save bread for dipping).
Combine all ingredients; heat.
Cool to room temperature, add chopped walnuts (optional).
Stuff bread with mixture.
Put lid on bread and wrap in foil.
Place in oven 2 hours at 325°.
Can be served with crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread to make the dip; refrigerate. Slice top of bread off and hollow out the inside, leaving about 1/4 inch thick shell.

Cut the excess bread into 1 inch cubes and surround the loaf with the bread pieces for dipping. For best results, mix the dip and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving. Fill the bread bowl just before serving.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Combine all ingredients using electric mixer.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Pour into 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° until a knife stuck in the middle is clean.
Brush brown sugar over top of pies and on crust.
This make 2 pies.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish the can of peas first, 1/2 can golden mushroom soup, 1/2 cup cheese, can of asparagus (drained), 1/2 can golden mushroom soup and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; moisten with a little of the milk.
Add melted margarine, eggs, remainder of milk, vanilla and coconut. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.
Bake in greased aluminum pie pans.
Will make its own crust.

title: chocolate spritz cookies
directions: Mix together; roll a piece of dough the size of a walnut in hands and press flat.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy macaroni-n-cheese
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box.
In glass bowl, place cheese (mashed a little) and milk in microwave and cook until cheese is melted, stirring at least once every minute.
It takes approximately 4 minutes to melt.
Add margarine and then noodles. It's ready to serve.
You can brown on top in oven if you would like.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake as for rolls until brown.
Layer cream cheese mixture over dough.
Put on raw vegetables.
Serve as appetizer.

title: will's tarragon chicken
directions: Brown salted chicken with 2 bay leaves and onion cut in slices.
The browner the better for flavor.
Stir in tarragon and pepper; add flour and chicken broth to thicken.
Add sour cream and pour over rice or egg noodles.

title: quick cherry salad
directions: Chill all and add banana just before serving.

title: auburn pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and egg yolks.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Beat all together. Stir in pineapple and nuts. Fold in egg whites carefully.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: grace kelley's irish scones
directions: In large bowl sift dry ingredients; add raisins.
Beat eggs, butter and milk together.
Fold into dry mixture.
Mix until well moistened - do not beat.
Pour into 9 x5-inch loaf pan which has been well greased.
Bake 350° for 50-60 minutes.
*Note - to make buttermilk:
1 1/2 c. milk and 1/4 c. vinegar.
Let stand awhile.

title: white poppy seed cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done with wooden pick.
Remove from pan to wire rack. Immediately brush warm cake with glaze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fry onion in 4 tablespoons butter; add flour and water.
When thick, add Cheez Whiz.
Combine sauce and broccoli; add eggs. Pour in a greased casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs, using the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: garmany school's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove from container and cook noodles in broth until tender, approximately 7 to 10 minutes. Remove chicken from bone and cut into small pieces.

title: kathy's pudding(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Combine in saucepan and cook over medium heat until it bubbles and thickens. Stir constantly. Spoon small amounts of hot mixture into egg and stir. Add egg to pudding. Cook 2 more minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and butter. Blend well. Line a bowl with vanilla wafers. Pour 1/2 pudding and spoon in 1 cup sliced drained strawberries. Put on another layer of wafers. Pour on pudding. Spoon in remaining strawberries. Add juice if desired.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Place peaches and juice (or strawberries) in saucepan with water, boil until tender, adding about 1/2 cup sugar to juice while cooking.
Put butter in bottom of baking dish and melt.
In small bowl mix flour, 1 cup sugar and milk together until smooth.
Pour this mixture into butter.
Spread peaches or strawberries evenly over mixture.
Add juice to dish.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown (approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: never fail icing
directions: Place egg whites, syrup and salt in medium bowl of mixer and whip at a high speed until it will stand in peaks.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and continue beating until sugar is well blended and does not taste grainy.
Add vanilla and spread on cake.
This recipe makes enough for large cake.

title: cousin hilda's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add and beat together well eggs, lemon extract and vanilla.
Cut up the cherries and pineapple; chop pecans.
Mix ingredients well, then add 2 cups plain flour.
Mix well.
Grease a tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Place in cold oven and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Store in covered container at least 3 days before cutting.
Delicious!

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients
well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry fig jelly
directions: Cook figs and sugar at rolling boil for 10 minutes. Add Jell-O and cook 10 more minutes. Then put in jars and seal. Makes 5 pints.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain and rinse dill pickles.
In pan, mix sugar, cider vinegar, water and pickling spice.
Simmer until clear.
Pour over pickles, repacked in jar, while hot.
Let stand 2 days in refrigerator.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: In saucepan, add water, sugar, lard, raisins, cloves, cinnamon and salt; boil for 5 minutes, then add 3 cups flour, soda and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook first 5 ingredients approximately 3 hours.
Add water, if necessary. Add chicken the last 1/2 hour. Serve soup in bowls.
In each individual bowl, add a sprinkle of Mozzarella cheese, a spoon of salsa and a spoon of sour cream. Stir until melted.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread on cooled crust. Arrange desired fruit on filling.

title: cinnamon chicken
directions: Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over crushed breadcrumbs. Beat egg with 1/4 cup Half and Half, salt and pepper. Roll chicken in egg mixture and then roll in crumb mixture. Brown chicken in oil and then arrange pieces in a glass 9 x 13 pan. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°. After about 15 minutes in the oven, baste with remaining 1/4 c. Half and Half. Remove cover the last few minutes of baking. Yummy! Serve with scalloped potatoes and fresh green beans.

title: hot vegetable dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk together, then add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling and then simmer for 10 minutes. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Dot with pats of butter and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 15 minute cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk; boil 1 minute.
Stir in oats, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: vanilla "philly" frosting
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, milk, vanilla and salt, mixing until well blended.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Fills and frosts two 8 or 9-inch cake layers.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes only until tender.
Cool, cube and measure. Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, remaining salt, onion and garlic powder.
Mix thoroughly, then fold into potatoes gently.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with shredded cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
At this point, it may be baked or refrigerated for later use.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly and slightly golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: irish swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 or 8 portions, brown in skillet and add ingredients and simmer on low for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter snacks
directions: Combine sugar and syrup until dissolved in pan.
Remove from heat and add butter and peanut butter.
Pour over wheat puffs. Drop by tablespoon and refrigerate.

title: macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
In a medium-sized bowl, combine 2 cups cheese and the macaroni; sprinkle into the pie plate.
Except for the remaining 1/4 cup cheese, beat the remaining ingredients until smooth for about 15 seconds in a blender on high speed (or for 1 minute in a large bowl with a hand beater).
Pour into the pie plate.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Salt chicken and place skin side down in shallow baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and brush both sides of chicken with mixture.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 45 minutes, turning and basting often, until tender.
Just before serving, put into a 400° oven for 10 minutes or broil 5 minutes for a crisp chicken (I do boneless, skinless chicken breasts this way, covered; delicious!).

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Frost the cookies while warm.

title: hamburger pie rosemarie
directions: Bake pie shell 10 minutes in 350° oven until brown.
Cook hamburger and separate until done.
Microwave broccoli and carrots until tender.
Combine hamburger (drained), vegetables, soup, mushrooms, Ricotta cheese and 1/2 of the Jack cheese.
Put mixture in pie shell.
Top with remaining Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until heated through and cheese melts.
(If desired, add corn, beans or potatoes to mixture before putting into pie shell.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook 2 minutes after it starts to boil.
Stir next 3 ingredients.
Beat with mixer well.
Cool until set.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain juice of pineapple.
Add Jell-O.
Warm over heat until Jell-O dissolves.
Mix pineapple and buttermilk.
Pour hot mixture over pineapple and buttermilk.
Add Cool Whip and blend until there are no lumps.
Pour in casserole dish and refrigerate.
Best if congealed overnight.

title: cranberries in the snow
directions: Cook cranberries in 3/4 c. water.
Add jell-o and sugar.

Mix well. Add pineapple and half the pecans. Pour into clear Pyrex dish. Refrigerate overnight. The next morning, prepare topping. Whip cream cheese, Cool Whip and marshmallow cream together. Spread over cranberry mixture and top with remaining pecans.

title: crab imperial
directions: Toss lightly with fork until well combined. Put in shallow pan (1-quart baking dish) or shells.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar, egg and cooking oil; mix.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; mix, but do not overbeat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over cooked chicken and place in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ding bats
directions: Melt butter, chopped nuts, chopped dates, 1 can coconut, sugar and vanilla.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in remaining can of coconut.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and shape into balls.
Brown in skillet; remove fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly, stirring constantly until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs; stir carefully until coated.
Simmer uncovered 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
(We use a crock-pot.)

title: june's fondue
directions: Rub pan with cut garlic cloves.
Leave in pan.
Add water and vinegar.
If desired, add chili powder.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Toss cheese with flour until cheese is coated with flour. Add cheese to liquid.
Stir until cheese melts and mixture starts to boil.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly until smooth.
Keep warm over candle or hot water.
Serve with cubes of toasted garlic bread or if you use chili powder, taco chips may be used.
Serve with a simple salad for a complete meal.

title: short-cut baked beans
directions: Mix beans and all other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: no calorie dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in quart jar.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Prepare instant pudding as directed. Add Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with graham crackers. Cover with pudding mixture.
Layer again with graham crackers and remaining pudding.
Top this with graham crackers. Spread canned frosting over top of graham crackers.
Chill before serving.

title: terry's gingerbread cookies
directions: Melt margarine in large stainless steel pan.
Add sugar, molasses and spices.
Stir over low heat until well blended.
Stir in egg and baking soda.
(Mixture will froth slightly.)
Add heavy cream and stir until well blended.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
(You may find it easier to mix in last cup of flour with hands.)
Cover dough and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Roll out desired amount and shape.
Bake at 350°.
Extra dough can be refrigerated for several weeks.

title: butterscotch delights
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Remove from heat, stir in nuts and noodles; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill 10 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.

title: open-faced apple pie
directions: Arrange apple slices in pie shell until full.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add half and half; mix well.
Cover apples with cream mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake for 30 minutes longer or until apples are tender.

title: bread sticks
directions: Cut frozen hot dog buns into thin strips.
Place on cookie sheet.
Melt margarine.
Pour over cut buns.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and crunchy.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix butter and sugar by hand (please wash them first!).
Have the flour measured; add it, a bit at a time.
Also add the nuts, alternating flour and nuts until done.
If the dough is very sticky, add a little more flour.
Wipe your hands off, then put a little flour on your hands as needed while you roll balls of dough (about the size of a walnut and 1-inch in diameter).
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes (until lightly browned).
Cool completely, then shake them in a Baggie of powdered sugar.
Recipe can be doubled for holiday baking.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind in food processor the squash, onions and green peppers. Add 1/2 cup salt.
Cover with cold water and let stand for 1 hour. Rinse and drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar and turmeric.
Boil mixture for 3 minutes.
Add squash mixture to liquids and simmer for 3 minutes.
Prepare 6 pint jars and seal.
This is great with pinto beans.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and margarine.
Blend until you have fine crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup of crumbs.
To remainder of crumbs, add buttermilk, soda and egg.
Mix well.
Pour batter into 2 (8-inch) greased pans.
Top with cup of reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm in center.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix margarine, onion, mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce together.
Split rolls and spread mix on bottom
layer. Layer ham and cheese next.
Place top on rolls and spread with more mix.
Wrap in foil and warm at 400° for 15 minutes until cheese melts.
Can be made ahead and placed in freezer.

title: turnip soup
directions: Cover vegetables with water and stew until soft. Blend vegetables along with cooking water. Add milk and heat. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet and sour microwave meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 20 meatballs. Place in 9-inch round glass baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave 8 to 10 minutes on Roast, stirring once.
Drain and let stand, covered, about 3 minutes.
During standing time for meatballs, microwave Sweet-Sour Sauce.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, salt, melted butter and sifted flour.
Beat 2 minutes with an electric mixer.
Pour into sizzling hot, well-greased muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve warm.

title: colonial damsel pie(served at king's arms tavern in williamsburg)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with mixer until pale yellow. Gradually add brown sugar, mixing well.
Mix in the butter.
Add the preserves.
Turn into the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until filling is almost firm.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
This may be frozen until needed.
Thaw at room temperature.

title: vegetable pizza(serves 40)
directions: Flatten rolls on large cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing until spreadable.
Spread mixture onto cooled rolls.
Top with finely chopped vegetables.
Cover with wrap and press vegetables into spread.
Cut into 40 pieces.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; add milk gradually and stir until smooth.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add small amount hot mixture to egg yolks; blend well.
Return to hot mixture. Cook until thickened, stirring over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Blend in vanilla, butter and salt.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes. Add coconut or bananas to the pudding at this time.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix with a whisk all ingredients together.
Put in a heavy saucepan; place on a medium temperature burner and cook until thick, stirring all the time, with the whisk (about 10 minutes). Pour into a 9 or 10-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder together until stiff.
Add sugar gradually and beat again.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Bake in greased 9-inch pie pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool for 2 hours.
Before serving, spread with whipped cream.

title: shell macaroni casserole
directions: Bring to boil and add macaroni.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: bottom round pot roast
directions: Place 30 x 18-inch piece of heavy aluminum foil in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place meat on foil and brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle soup mix over top of meat and spread mushroom soup over meat.
Fold foil over meat and seal securely.
Cook in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain and reserve pineapple liquid.
Combine first 4 ingredients plus pineapple juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Let cool.
When cool, add fruit, nuts and Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: jamaican jerk chicken skewers(instead of skewers, cut a whole chicken into pieces)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in a glass or stainless steel bowl.
Mix well.
Rinse the chicken under cold water, pat dry with paper towels and place in a large sealable plastic bag.
Pour in the marinade, seal the bag, then tip and turn it, so all the chicken is coated.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours, up to 25 hours.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Sift
flour,
salt and powder.	Cut in shortening.
Add milk, all at once and mix.
Divide dough in 2 parts.
Roll out in rectangle
x
12-inch).
Divide sausage.
Spread over dough. Roll up and wrap in wax paper.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: pineapple pecan cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and frost with canned frosting.

title: barbecued ground beef
directions: Brown meat in its own fat until light brown.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: southern buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in butter.
Stir in buttermilk. Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead lightly.
Roll 1-inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake at 450° until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Smother in butter and sink your teeth in.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown the pork chops and place on top of mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, covered, at 325°.
Serves 4.
(May need to add water while baking.)

title: mini cherry pockets
directions: Heat oven to 450°, place pie crusts on cutting board; remove plastic sheets.
Cut each pie crust into quarters making 8 wedges. Top 1/2 of each triangle with 2 tablespoons pie filling.
Fold remaining pie crust half over filling.
Press edges with fork to seal.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 11-15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Makes 8 pockets.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients 2 minutes after coming to a boil. Line rimmed cookie sheet with foil.
Spread out graham crackers and spread the mix over them.
Put nuts on top.
Bake at 350° about 7 to 10 minutes.
Cut apart and drain on paper towels.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all together and shape into balls.
Melt 6 ounce package chocolate chips and 1/2 stick paraffin.
Dip balls into mixture. Cool on wax paper.

title: mrs. lincoln's white cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder; remove 2 Tbsp. and set aside.
Add sifted ingredients, alternating with milk, to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and almond extract.
Combine almonds with reserved flour and add to batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add in salt.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake at 375° until a cake tester comes out clean, about 55 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: carrot chiffon cake
directions: Separate the eggs and add a pinch of salt to whites; set aside.
Beat yolks and add sugar, cake flour, carrots, orange peel, ginger, cinnamon and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into egg yolk mixture.
Turn into a 9-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet salties
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening in heavy saucepan over low flame.
Add pretzels and peanuts; mix well.
Spread into a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Chill 20 minutes or until firm.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.
Very easy to make and very yummy too!

title: pork chops with cabbage german style
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon shortening in large frying pan.
Brown chops on both sides over medium heat, turning chops only once.
Add cloves, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 cup water.
Cover tightly and cook over medium heat 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone; cut in pieces and spread in baking pan.
Take two cans of cream of chicken soup and mix with milk. Heat and pour over chicken in baking pan.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Take chicken broth and stuffing mix; add to onions and celery until you get desired thickness.
Spread over chicken.
Bake in oven at 400° until brown.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Combine soup with wine and pour over beef in large pan.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add water if need additional liquid after first hour.

title: spanish rice(great low-fat recipe)
directions: Combine tomatoes, water, onion and bouillon in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Make sure you have a full 2 1/2 c. of liquid.
If not, add water to total 2 1/2 cups.
Bring liquid to boil in saucepan.
Immediately add rice and cover, then lower heat to simmer for 20 minutes.
DO NOT LIFT LID!
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: rum punch
directions: Mix and serve in punch bowl.

title: mallow fruit salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat buttermilk and pudding. Mix on medium speed for 1 minute. Let stand for 5 minutes. Fold in fruit cocktail, oranges, marshmallows and whipped cream. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve. Serves 8 to 10.

title: homemade amish noodles
directions: Beat eggs lightly and add water and salt.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface 3 to 5 minutes.
Divide into 3 pieces and roll out paper thin.
Let dry about an hour.
Roll up jelly roll fashion and cut crosswise into strips of desired thickness.
Spread loosely to dry.

title: railroad cornbread pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add tomato soup, water, pepper, salt, chili powder, green pepper and corn.
Put in baking dish. Mix corn meal, sugar, flour, egg, milk and oil.
Mix this well. Drop by spoonfuls over the beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bread is golden brown.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add chicken, stirring to coat. Heat 1-inch vegetable oil in heavy skillet.
Cook chicken until lightly browned.
Drain.
Drain pineapple; set aside.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons oil until tender.
Add carrots, water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, 2 tablespoons cornstarch and ginger. Stir in catsup, vinegar and 1 tablespoon soy sauce, stirring well. Gradually stir cornstarch mixture into vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in chicken, green pepper and pineapple.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: glorified rice cream
directions: Cook rice in water until almost done, then add milk, sugar, salt and flavor.
Cook until liquid is absorbed.
Add maraschino cherries and 1 can crushed pineapple (or any fruit goes).
When cool, fold in Cool Whip.
Top with Danish Dessert.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Gradually add flour and small amounts of cream cheese.
Add flavorings and Dream Whip.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: memaw's macaroni and egg salad
directions: Cook seashells or elbow macaroni according to package instructions.
Mix with remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve on lettuce or other greens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pralines
directions: Line pans with honey grahams.
Bring margarine and sugar to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
When bubbles stop, add pecans.
Spread on graham crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool for a few minutes.
Break apart and enjoy.

title: hot turkey sandwich (low-fat)
directions: Layer bread and put heated turkey slices on top.
Heat gravy and cover the sandwich.
Add cranberry sauce.

title: apricot bars
directions: First Layer:
Cream 3/4
cup
oleo
and 1 cup of sugar, then add flour, salt,
soda,
coconut and nuts.	Mix well with your hands.
Press 3 cups
into	bottom of pan (like a crust). Cook 10 minutes at 400°.

title: honey walnut bread
directions: Boil milk, honey and sugar; stir to dissolve.
Cool.
Beat in margarine and egg yolks.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and add to batter.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased, floured loaf pans.
Let stand for 15 minutes before putting in oven.
Bake at 325° until tested done.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium pan.
Cook over low heat until well mixed.
Let cool.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream the butter; add brown sugar.
Beat.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all at once until smooth.
If need be, add more milk. Three envelopes Nestle chocolate may be used instead of unsweetened chocolate.

title: green chile stew
directions: Cook chicken breasts in 2 quarts water.
When done, cool and cut up in small pieces.
Mix with other ingredients; cook until done.

title: "philly" brunch quiche
directions: Heat cream cheese and milk over low heat; stir until smooth. Saute onion in margarine.
Gradually add cream cheese sauce to eggs; stir in onion, ham, pimento and seasonings.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Take care not to overbake.
The center will be slightly soft when the quiche is done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; then add the rest.
Grease well and flour 3 loaf pans or 1 tube pan and 1 loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (or less).
Don't overcook.

title: baked ziti and cheese
directions: Prepare ziti per package.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Blend slowly with hot water and then add vanilla. Add salad dressing last. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until center is done.

title: meat stuffing(10 to 12 pound turkey)
directions: Combine meat, bay leaves, salt, pepper and onion.
Cover with water and cook slowly until meat is browned.
Drain liquid from this mixture.
Add cracker crumbs and mix well.
Allow to cool! Add sage.
Allow to cool!
Now your turkey is ready to be stuffed. If there is any stuffing left, you can combine it with mashed potatoes and use as a filling for a pie which is baked the same way as a fruit pie would be.

title: golden apple spice cake
directions: Combine flour, oil, sugar, baking soda and seasonings; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick test comes out clean (insert in center of cake).
Cool completely before frosting.
Spread with icing and let harden. Makes about 12 servings.

title: one great dip
directions: Mix well and enjoy.

title: doves with rice in wine
directions: Saute the rice in the butter until brown, not burned.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.

title: dolly mcclintock's johnny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl (or as recipe states, "stir up and bake."
Bake at least 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: fruit juice shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend 30 seconds at high speed.
Serve at once.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients in casserole dish.
Saute butter and crackers for topping. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: And a Twinkle from your Eye,

title: chocolate marshmallow cake
directions: Boil butter and water.
Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Pour hot mixture over dry.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still warm, spread over cake. Mix ingredients for frosting and spread on warm cake.

title: play dough
directions: Combine water, cooking oil and food coloring in saucepan.
Add flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Cook on medium heat until dough is right consistency for use (3 to 5 minutes).
Store in plastic bag or plastic bowl.
Needs no refrigeration.

title: scrambled eggs deluxe
directions: In a large skillet, cook potato patties in 1 tablespoon margarine on 1 side for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
In same skillet, cook onion in remaining margarine.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, milk and soup; beat well.
Stir in mushrooms, pimiento and pepper.
Add to onion in skillet.
Cook until eggs are nearly set; do not stir.
Then lift and fold partially so underneath can cook.
Cool eggs slightly.
Spoon egg mixture into 3 greased individual casseroles.
Arrange sausages and potato patties, browned side up, in casserole.
Seal with foil and freeze.

title: french vanilla delight
directions: Place enough graham crackers to line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix milk and pudding, beating until thick.

Spread enough (or half) of the pudding mixture over the graham crackers. Place another layer of graham crackers and another layer (the rest) of the vanilla pudding. Chill. Top with milk chocolate frosting before serving.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan. Boil until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from fire and add 1/2 teaspoon of soda.
Pour over 4 quarts of popped corn while foaming.

title: mushroom cheeseburger casserole
directions: Butter pan and press canned biscuits around bottom and sides. Mix all other ingredients together (except cheese).
Pour into pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover biscuits with tinfoil.
Bake an additional 5 minutes when tin removed.

title: prune whip
directions: Whip jello to break it all up real good.
Mix everything together thoroughly.
It gets better after it sets for a few hours.

title: great cookies
directions: Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: In pan, add jello and pudding to 2 1/2 cups water and bring to a boil, stirring with a whisk.
Put in refrigerator to cool and thicken.
Slice berries into bottom of crust and pour cooled mixture over top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Dip in chocolate mixture.

title: southern baked corn
directions: Mix in bowl the corn and cornbread mix.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Melt margarine and add margarine and sour cream.
Mix well by hand until all lumps are gone.
Pour into casserole dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set and knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sausage fondue
directions: Arrange half of bread in single layer in bottom of large, flat-bottomed baking dish.
Cook sausage in skillet until slightly browned.
Drain and layer over bread.
Top with layer of cheese, then another layer of bread.
Beat eggs and mustard.
Add milk and blend.
Pour over bread.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: In a heavy, non-iron skillet, melt the butter and cook the cabbage over medium heat. Saute it for 5 minutes while tossing it in the butter.

Pour in the cream. Season with salt and pepper. Bring quickly back to the boil; cover pan and reduce heat. Cook over low heat for 15 minutes until tender, but not soft. Sprinkle with caraway seed before serving, if desired. Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine
raisins
and
pineapple
and
soak
overnight. Cream butter and sugar
until
light.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after
each.
Add
jam.
Sift dry ingredients together and
add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in pecans, raisins and pineapple.
Bake
in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Ice
with Jam Cake Icing.
Cake is better if made several days before eating.

title: quick caramel coffee ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small saucepan, melt the margarine. Coat the bottom and sides of a 12 cup fluted tube pan with 2 tablespoons of the margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of the nuts over bottom of the greased pan.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to remaining margarine; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits; cut each biscuit in half and shape into a ball.
Place 20 balls in bottom of pan; drizzle with half of the caramel over the balls. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert immediately on waxed paper and remove from pan. Makes 10 servings.

title: chili
directions: Stir-fry first 3 ingredients in sprayed pan.
Combine everything in one pot and simmer for 30 minutes.
Ready to serve. Serves 6.

title: garden fresh stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Add green peppers and water.
Mix lightly.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until meat is tender.
Stir in mushrooms and tomato wedges.
Continue to cook 10 minutes.

title: chicken ala can
directions: Heat soup, water and rice.
Add 2 cans of chicken.
Crumble in a few onions.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Add onions on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: clam patty(serves 6)
directions: Drain clams and combine with mashed potatoes, butter, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Shape into 12 patties of equal size.
Fry in hot fat until lightly brown on both sides.

title: budin de platano(banana and pineapple pudding)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, beat whole eggs and egg yolks.
Stir in milk and first 1/4 cup sugar.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat for about 10 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened and coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat; stir in rum.
Chill.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water. Slice strawberries into jello.
Mix well.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Add 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: mom's peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, Karo syrup and butter to soft crack boil.
Add peanuts and bring to hard crack boil.
Take off stove; add teaspoon of soda.
Drop or spread on greased pan or wax paper. Cool and break up.

title: hot dried beef dip
directions: Mix all together. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or golden brown in oven ready bowl. Serve hot with crackers.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Spread a thin layer of cream cheese over entire side of ham and sprinkle green onion on edge of ham (shortways).
Roll into a tube and slice to desired thickness.
Serve.

title: steak and tomatoes
directions: Arrange meat in crock pot. Cover with soup mix, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, and vinegar, oil and remaining ingredients. Stir...Cover. Start cooking on HIGH for 30 minutes, then cut down to LOW (and go to work). Simmer all day (or 3 hours if you're in a hurry). Serve over rice.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cook first seven ingredients until tender; turn off heat.
Add soup and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Can be reheated immediately or saved for later.
Do not boil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Cut garlic clove in half and rub the interior of blender jar with cut sides.
Chop the tomatoes and 1 cucumber and put them and the onion in the blender jar.
Blend 1/2 minute.
Add oil, Tabasco, lemon juice and vinegar.
Whirl at high speed for 1 minute.
Chill thoroughly.
Before serving, dice the remaining cucumber and stir it and the green pepper into the soup.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place an ice cube in each soup bowl.
Pour the soup over the ice and garnish with one lemon slice and a sprinkling of parsley.
Serves 6.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add oil and vanilla.
Beat again; stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Continue beating, then add apples and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate egg nog
directions: Mix and chill egg nog, chocolate milk and creme de cacao.
When ready to serve, stir in whipped cream.
Garnish with shaved chocolate.
Makes ten 1/2-cup servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add cracker crumbs and butter (mix crumbs and butter together first).
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Top with cornflakes and butter slices. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Place cranberries in a 10-inch greased pie plate.
Sprinkle with nuts and white sugar.
Pour melted butter on top.
In bowl, mix eggs, brown sugar, flour and melted butter.
Pour into pie plate.
Do not mix the 2 layers. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 1-quart casserole with Pam.
Add 1/2 of dry macaroni; cover with 1/2 of cheese.
Add rest of macaroni.
Add rest of cheese.
Dot with oleo or butter.
Add 2 cups milk.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Put lid on casserole and bake 45 minutes in preheated oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Sprinkle 4 teaspoons salt over sliced squash and onions. Leave for 1 hour.
Drain well.
Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil.
Add all ingredients.
Bring back to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple and one cup nuts.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: pecan squash
directions: Cook squash with butter, Tang, salt and pepper as directed on squash package.
Stir in pecans.

title: angel hair pasta with basil-tomato sauce
directions: Heat the oil over medium heat.
Add the garlic and shallot and saute until the garlic is golden and the shallot wilted.
Add the tomatoes.
Season with salt, pepper and basil.
Meanwhile, cook the pasta in an uncovered pot in rapidly boiling water for about 1 to 2 minutes.
Test it after 1 minute for "al dente" (firm to the bite) texture.
Drain the pasta, reserving 2 tablespoons of the water it was cooked in.
Add the pasta and the reserved water to the tomato sauce.
Stir gently to coat the pasta with the sauce.
Remove to a serving platter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: braised carrots
directions: Place the carrots in a saucepan with the salt and 1 inch of boiling water.
Cook, covered, until almost tender, about 6 minutes.

Drain if there is any water remaining, then set aside. In a small skillet, saute the onion rings in butter until limp. Stir the flour into the carrots, then add to this the onion rings. Cook until the carrots begin to brown, then add bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly until carrots are tender, not more than 10 minutes.
Add chopped parsley.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and peppers.
Add cooked macaroni and 1/2 of cheese.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Cook water and Crisco in pan until it simmers; cool 5 minutes. Add eggs (beat in one at a time).
Spread on lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with 2 cups milk.
Add vanilla pudding and milk. Beat until thickened.
Spread on crust, then top with Cool Whip. Drizzle with Hershey's syrup.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cornmeal, plain flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda. In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients. Add to dry ingredients and stir only until moistened. Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan or 10-inch heavy iron skillet. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bread is golden brown or tests done.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain the kidney beans and rinse.
Add the celery, pepper and onion.
Drain the green beans and wax beans.
Mix all vegetables together in bowl.
Measure vinegar, sugar, water and oil.
Heat and pour over vegetables.
Let stand in the refrigerator overnight.

title: peach daiquiri ice
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice.
In a blender, combine peach slices, sugar, rum, lime peel, lime juice and reserved peach juice.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into loaf pan.
Cover and freeze for at least 4 hours until firm. Let stand at room temperature before serving.

title: buttered cabbage
directions: In a large Dutch oven, add cabbage to boiling salted water. Cook, uncovered, on low for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring frequently. Drain cabbage and toss with butter and pepper before serving.

title: vidalia onion peel
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Place onions in pastry shell.
Combine eggs, salt, paprika and milk and mix well. Pour egg liquid over onions.
Bake at 375F for 25-20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin log
