directions: Combine all ingredients, except walnuts and powdered sugar, and beat until smooth.
Line an 11 x 14-inch jelly roll pan. Spray with Pam.
Pour batter into pan.
Sprinkle with ground walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: poor man's goodie(donut holes)
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Add milk to make a workable dough.
Roll and slice in small pieces.
Heat oil to medium high. Drop pieces into hot oil, stir until light brown.
Drain on paper towel and then roll in sugar.
(Do not use butter Crisco to cook in.)

title: rocky road bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips, milk and margarine together over hot water in a large bowl.
When melted, add the peanuts and marshmallows.
Mix thoroughly and pour into buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Chill thoroughly and use a very sharp knife to cut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: whacky cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Make 3 wells and add vanilla, vinegar and oil.
Pour cold water over all and mix well. This may be mixed and baked in same pan or grease and flour 2 (9-inch) layer pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter to generously cover skillet. Place potatoes in skillet over medium heat. Put sugar and cinnamon on potatoes. Fry like slow fried potatoes. Cook until tender. Serve hot.

title: crab canapes
directions: Combine cheeses, lemon juice, crab meat and salt; mix well. Spread each toast round with mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil until bubbly, about 3 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen canapes.

title: savory chicken vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, bring stock to a boil.
Add the garlic, savory, basil, celery seed, pepper and ginger.
Reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes; cook for 10 minutes.
Add onion; cook for 5 minutes or until tender.
Add chicken, tomato, corn, peas and beans.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until vegetables are all tender.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles.
Beat eggs and remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella.
Layer half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the Ricotta filling and half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce.
Repeat steps.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: creamy tuna macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together flour, mayonnaise, onion and mustard.
Gradually stir in milk.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat for 3 minutes, or until mixture thickens. Gradually stir in cheese.
In greased 2-quart casserole, stir together cheese mixture, cooked macaroni and tuna.
In pan, melt margarine and stir in bread crumbs; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Grate cheese and put 3/4 of it on top of first mixture in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and place remaining cheese on top.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together and roll in cabbage leaves.
Add 1 can tomatoes over top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: buffalo wings(a real party treat!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, Tabasco and vinegar; dip in wings and put on greased pan.
Sprinkle with Ranch mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
May serve with Ranch dressing to dip chicken wings in, but I prefer without.

title: frosted orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large bowl.
Gently stir in sherbet, pineapple and oranges.
Pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine orange juice, egg, sugar and flour in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Allow to cool.
Prepare topping mix according to package directions.
Fold into cooked orange mixture; spread evenly over salad.
Cover and chill overnight.
Yields 12 servings.

title: corn o'brien
directions: Saute celery in butter for 5 minutes.
Add corn, pimento and salt.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve.

title: mother's banana pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar, then add eggs and mix well.
Next add vanilla and stir in milk, being sure to mix well.
Cook over double boiler, stirring constantly until thick.
Layer bowl with vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Pour hot pudding over bananas and cookies.

title: white trash
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Melt chocolate in microwave.
Pour over mixture.
Coat well.
Pour on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Break in pieces.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Rinse and pat chicken dry.
Place in pie pan large enough for all pieces.
Pour taco sauce over chicken, turning pieces to coat well.
Cover with foil loosely.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken pieces and roll in crushed corn chips, coating well.
Place in lightly greased baking dish and bake for 40 to 45 minutes, turning chicken often for the first 20 minutes.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: You will need 2 loaf pans.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned fruit and maraschino cherries.
Mix fruit, sour cream, coconut and marshmallows together.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: maggie's mexican salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain and allow to cool. In large bowl mix together remaining ingredients; toss in pasta. Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Drain.
Brown sausage.
Mix together squash and onion mixture, cheese, eggs and crackers. Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Reserve some dried beef for outside of cheese ball.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; crumble as it fries.
Drain and rinse sausage.
In a saucepan combine soups, tomatoes and sausage; heat thoroughly.
Serve warm with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: babka-polish bread
directions: Scald milk; carefully stir 1/2 cup flour into hot milk.
When smooth and cool, add yeast softened in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Set aside to rise.
Add salt to egg yolks and beat until thick.
Add to yeast mixture the butter, sugar, beaten egg yolks and cardamon.
Beat with spoon thoroughly.
Slowly add the remaining 1 1/2 cups flour and the raisins, nuts and cherries. Knead with hand until dough no longer sticks to fingers.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again about 1 hour. Bake in loaf, tube or round pan for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp gumbo soup
directions: Make a roux, which will be the shortening and flour (it will make a paste). Add garlic; brown, stirring constantly. Add the bell pepper, onions and celery, stir thoroughly to coat. Add the tomatoes and okra, then slowly add water. Season with seasonings to your taste and add the seafood of your choice. Simmer for 30 minutes, serve over rice.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sift cake flour into small bowl and set aside.

With mixer on medium-high speed, cream butter, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in medium mixing bowl until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Stop mixer once or twice to scrape bowl with a rubber spatula. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat on medium after each addition, about 10 seconds, scraping bowl each time.
Mix 30 seconds longer.

title: russian rocks
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and allspice.
Add 3 eggs to the butter and sugar mixture.
Add all other ingredients.
Use a teaspoon to drop the cookies onto a greased cookie sheet.
Keep the spoon moist so the batter will not stick.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until the cookies are brown.

title: susan's cranberry ice cream
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Fold in can of cranberries and crushed, drained pineapple.
Mix in Cool Whip and walnuts until thoroughly mixed.
Either spread ingredients in a flat cake sheet or put two teaspoons each in cupcake papers.
Keep frozen until you are ready to eat.
Goes great with turkey.

title: chocolate rocky road cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and water; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup marshmallows, 1/4 cup chocolate chips and 1/4 cup nuts and fold in.
Pour into prepared 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with remaining nuts, chips and marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Drizzle a chocolate glaze over cake while warm.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix rice with oleo in crock-pot.
Stir to coat rice thoroughly.
Add all remaining ingredients, except some almonds and onions to sprinkle on top.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours, on high for 2 to 3 hours.

title: pickled peach salad
directions: Use juice from peaches and cherries. Add water or orange juice to make 4 cups liquid.
Heat 2 cups liquid and dissolve the gelatin.
Add the other 2 cups liquid.
Chill until it begins to jell.
Cut up fruit and add
marmalade and nuts to gelatin mixture.
Pour into a large ring and allow to set. Serves 12 to 16.

title: chicken or pork adobo
directions: Wash chicken pieces; remove skin.
Mix all of the ingredients in a large skillet.
Cook on high-medium until boiling.
Remove froth when boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Continue to cook until meat is tender (approximately 45 minutes).
Do not let skillet dry out.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: sweet 9 day pickles
directions: Soak cukes in salt water strong enough to float an egg for 3 days, then drain and soak in clear water for another 3 days, changing water each day.
On 7th day, slice thick and simmer for 3 hours in solution made of equal parts vinegar and water and 2 tablespoons powdered alum.
Drain and pour over cukes the following solution for the next 3 days, heating the solution each day:
7 pounds sugar, 2 pints white vinegar, 1 pint water, 1 ounce cassia bud, 1 ounce whole allspice or stick cinnamon.
After 9th day, seal in jars.
Use small cukes, not tiny and don't let them stand before soaking.
Apple vinegar may be used.

title: 1-2-3 donuts
directions: Separate biscuits; cut with donut cutter.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Take out and cool slightly.
Roll in sugar.

title: graham cracker salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: grilled peanut butter sandwich(for kids)
directions: Put butter on bread, then honey and then peanut butter.
Put toast in the oven and brown or toast.

title: old-fashioned ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Add milks.
Freeze according to freezer directions. Add crushed pineapple or other fruits for variety.

title: cobble stone candy
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water and stir until smooth.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in an 8-inch square pan lined with foil.
Let stand until firm and cut into squares.
Makes 1 2/3 pounds.

title: cheese soup
directions: Note:
Prepare as listed or it will curdle.

title: deviled macaroni salad
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil with salt.
Add macaroni slowly and stir frequently.
Cook about 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain thoroughly and rinse with hot water.
Cool.
Mash 2 eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Combine with cooled macaroni and chill. Garnish with remaining egg, sliced.
Makes 8 generous servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In a heavy bottom saucepan or cast-iron skillet, cook brown sugar and butter over low heat until melted and bubbly; stir until blended.
In blender, combine milk, cornstarch and egg yolks. Blend.
Stir into butter-sugar mixture and cook on medium heat until at a rolling boil.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Use the egg whites to make meringue.

title: corn pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Mix in corn, salt, pepper and flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into corn mixture. Fry in bacon fat (or butter/oil) until golden.
Turn and do other side.
Serves 4 to 5 people.
They puff up nicely.

title: presto stromboli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Unroll pizza crust and gently stretch in 2 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange meat over dough, leaving 2-inches clear around edges.
Top cheese over meat, also leaving edges clear.
Starting at long edge, roll up loosely.
Pinch to seal seam.
Press ends with fork and turn under.
Place seam-side down on cooke sheet.
With a sharp knife, cut 3 diagonal slits on top for steam to escape.
Brush lightly with water.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour pan.
Mix everything together; blend well.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cook rice as directed.
Cook broccoli until done.
Mix together cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, rice, broccoli, 1 cup of broth and add deboned chicken.
Pour into a casserole dish.
In a separate bowl melt 1 stick of butter and add stuffing to it.
Sprinkle over top of mixture and bake until hot and brown on top at 375°.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup and cheese in casserole dish.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake at 375° until onions are slightly browned.

title: potato and chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes and chicken.
Add salt, pepper and flour.
Melt butter and add soup and milk.
Pour over the other ingredients.
Top with crumbled potato chips or buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° with cover on.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stuffed veal roast(pieczen cieleca)
directions: Wash meat and wipe dry.
Fix stuffing mix as directed.
Fill pocket with stuffing and fasten with skewer.
Brush meat with melted butter and salt and sprinkle with marjoram.
Roast, uncovered, for 3 hours at 325°.
Cover during last half hour.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes and mix.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoons.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Beat egg whites, sugar, lemon juice and strawberries.
Beat this for 10 minutes.
Add Cool Whip and fold into mixture.
Freeze.
Serve slightly frozen.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Remove the grape leaves from the jar (don't tear them) and set them in some cool water to soak away some of the saltiness. Save the brine for later!

title: highland pot roast
directions: Brown roast in shortening in Dutch oven over medium heat. Arrange vegetables, except mushrooms, around roast.
Add seasonings.
Arrange apricots and mushrooms over roast.
Top with catsup; cover.
Bake in 325° oven for 2 hours or until tender, basting occasionally.
Yields 8 servings.

title: simple lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: tuscany bread
directions: Spread bread with butter and garlic.
Toast in oven.
Top with pesto.
Add half the cheese, spinach and then the remaining cheese.
Scatter chopped tomatoes across the top and sprinkle with basil and oregano.
Bake in oven 5 minutes at 375 degrees.
Cut slices in half and garnish plate with lemon wedges.

title: watergate cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large mixer bowl. Then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured layer pans, sheet cake pan or Bundt pan until done.
Cool 15 minutes on rack. Turn out and cool thoroughly.
Frost.

title: sylvia's surprise
directions: Cook onion and carrots in oil until done.
Add ham; mix together.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cooked rice and mix together. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple cake dessert
directions: Bake Jiffy cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and cool.
Drain pineapple well and spread over cooled cake.
Prepare vanilla pudding as directed.
Add 4 ounces cream cheese (use mixer).
Add nuts, saving enough to use on top of Cool Whip.
Pour over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining nuts. Refrigerate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Make pudding.
Pour over fruit and leave overnight in refrigerator. Drain and serve.
(If doubling recipe, 1 package of pudding mix will be enough.)

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Remove skin from chicken breast and cut each in halves. Place half between wax paper, pound until 1/4 inches.
Coat with flour.
Heat 2 tbsp. oil in a 12 inch skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook chicken until done and light brown.
About 4 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken to warm plates.
Heat remaining margarine in same skillet until melted.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and garnish with parsley and lemon slices.
Serve with hot cooked spaghetti.

title: chicken breasts in cider
directions: Place 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat for 2 minutes or until a drop of water sizzles on surface.
Reduce heat to medium; put in chicken breasts.
Brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add cider and orange juice concentrate. Cover pan and reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 30 minutes, boiling occasionally.
Remove chicken breasts to serving dish.
Add raisins to skillet; bring liquid to a boil.
Boil until slightly reduced.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with orange rinds and almonds.
Serve with rice pilaf.
Serves 4.

title: chicken cheese elegant
directions: Skin chicken breasts.
Place in large casserole or roaster, bone side down.
Do not stack.
Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Slice green onions over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken.
Mix soups together.
Spoon over chicken covering completely.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix jello, hot water, sugar, lemon juice and rind; simmer 10 minutes, then cool.
Allow to set, but not solid.
Whip condensed milk that has been chilled for 24 hours.
Mix together and put in buttered dish (9 x 13-inch) with layers of graham crackers or vanilla wafers.

title: three bean salad
directions: First drain all the vegetables.
Mix all of the rest of ingredients, pour over vegetables mix and marinate overnight. Stir occasionally.
Serve cold.

title: joyce's mexican corn bread
directions: Grease an 8 inch square pan. or a 12 cup muffin tin, or 14 stick pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients to a simmer, not a boil.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat thoroughly.

title: lipton onion sticks
directions: Mix softened butter and onion soup.
Spread slices of bread with mixture.
Cut each slice into 5 strips.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 10 minutes until golden at 375°.

title: good ole crock-pot stew
directions: Cut meat and vegetables into large pieces.
Combine all ingredients (except peas) in crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.
Add peas 1/2 hour before serving.
Serves 6 (1/2 cup).

title: chili powder
directions: Pull
off
and	discard
stems	and seeds from chilies. Break up pods and grind finely to make 1/3 cup (avoid breathing powder).
Mix
chilies with remaining ingredients.	Store airtight.
Use in chili recipes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: In blender, blend eggs, then buttermilk and then remaining ingredients for approximately 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell. Bake on middle rack for approximately 55 minutes at 375°, or until brown on top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Put half of the
Tater Tots in a 9 x 13-inch pan; put half of the hamburger in.
Use rest of the Tater Tots and hamburger.
Mix soup, milk and cheese in a pan until cheese starts to melt.
Pour over Tater Tots and hamburger. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: krispie milk-chocolate chip cookies
directions: P.S.
Two cups M&M's may be substituted for chocolate chips.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together. Add other ingredients. Mix well and chill.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, cube and save broth.
Saute onions and celery in a small amount of oil or butter.
Add chili powder, pimentos and soups; simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste and simmer 30 minutes.

title: ricotta puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon 1 teaspoon of batter into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
If you like, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: herbed crab spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and herbs (such as lemon thyme, Italian parsley and chives), and spread in a pie plate.
Top with the crab meat, then the sauce.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with fresh herbs. Serve with crackers.

title: baptist pie
directions: In blender place oranges and pineapples; blend for a few seconds. Empty into bowl and add milk and lemon juice. Mix well; fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crusts. Garnish with pecans. Chill 2 hours.

title: mayo-parmesan bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, spread onto sliced bread.
Broil until light brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, debone and cut into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave for 5 to 10 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: candied pecan
directions: In first bowl, put sugar, salt, and cinnamon.
In second bowl, beat egg white and cold water until frothy.
Toss pecans in egg white mixture and coat pecans.
Top with dry mixture.
Coat and mix well.
Spread on a non-stick cookie sheet.
Bake at 225 degrees for 1 hour.
Turn frequently.
Cool.
Store in air tight container.

title: quick peanut butter cookies(no flour)
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl; mix well.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking pan.
Press each ball with fork in crisscross design.
Put in preheated 325° oven and bake 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: miracle cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 9-inch dish, allowing it to cover bottom and grease sides of dish.
Prepare batter of sugar, flour, milk, powder and vanilla.
Sprinkle salt.
Pour batter into buttered dish.
Over the batter, spread 1 can of fruit.
While preparing, bring to a boil:
1 cup fruit liquid, 1/4 to 1 cup sugar (according to how tart fruit is), 2 tablespoons of butter.
Pour this over top of fruit in dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pudding goodie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Bisquick, brown sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat 1 cup powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Fold 1 cup Cool Whip into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over baked layer.
Mix chocolate pudding mix with 1 1/2 cups milk until it is thick.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Mix vanilla pudding mix with remaining 1 1/2 cups milk until thick.
Pour over chocolate pudding layer. Fold 1 tablespoon powdered sugar into the remaining Cool Whip and spread over top of all layers.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Cut and serve.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and diced bacon.
Drain.
In a large pot, combine all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes or bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until creamy. Beat in sugars, egg, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla until well blended.
Mix in flour until thoroughly combined.
Form mixture into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip tines of fork into flour and flatten dough in a criss-cross pattern.
Bake at 375° 7-9 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo, cheese, and eggs.
Fold in broccoli.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Finely crush crackers.
Add finely chopped pecans.
Mix together in a small bowl the sugar, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar mixture and beat until eggs are glass white.
Fold in pecans and cracker mix.
Put in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool completely and top with whipped cream.
Keep in icebox.

title: rare sour cream fudge recipe
directions: Grease an 8-inch square cake pan and set aside.
Combine first 5 ingredients in medium heavy saucepan.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, covered closely for about 3 minutes so steam can dissolve sugar crystals on pan sides.
Uncover and boil on medium heat to 236° on candy thermometer or until a little of the mixture dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and let stand for 15 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add flavoring; beat until mixture starts to lose its gloss (about 8 minutes).
Stir in the candied cherries and walnuts and quickly pour into a greased shallow pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields about 1 1/2 pounds of fudge.

title: luscious banana cake
directions: Combine the preceding ingredients together in mixing bowl; beat until creamy.
Add sour cream-baking soda mixture at last, just combining.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan, 9 x 13-inch or 2 (8 or 9-inch) round pans.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes until light brown and springy to touch.
Cool.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top or spread buttercream icing on it.
It is very good with a bit of allspice and cinnamon blended in with the buttercream icing.

title: chicken divan(serves 5 to 6.)
directions: Place chicken breasts in large saucepan.
Add water, carrot, celery tops, salt, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Cover saucepan. Heat to boiling, then simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Cool chicken in broth.
Remove skin from chicken and cut into thin slices.
Strain broth into measuring cup.
Add water if necessary to make 1 cup.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour until bubbly.
Stir in chicken broth, milk and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils 1 minute.
To half the sauce mixture, add grated cheese.
Lay broccoli spears in shallow broiler-proof dish. Top with chicken slices.
Spoon plain sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese sauce.
Broil about 6 inches from the source of heat for 5 minutes or until top is golden.

title: high protein cookies
directions: Put sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in kettle.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into buttered sheet pan.
(Cool and cut.)

title: scalloped broccoli
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli and noodles according to package directions; drain.
In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup and milk together until smooth.
Stir in broccoli, noodles, cheese, pepper and mushrooms.
Combine crumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10.

title: crazy pudding
directions: In bottom of a loaf pan, put the raisins.
Cream together sugar and oleo.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Scrape out of bowl and add to raisins.
Add sauce.

title: copper pennies
directions: Drain carrots and set aside. Chop green pepper and onion.
Add all ingredients except carrots and mix well. Add carrots and marinate for several hours or overnight. Drain and serve.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Boil gizzards until tender and chop.
Reserve water they were boiled in.
Add to broth onion, celery and chicken bouillon cubes. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Mix all together and add cornbread cake and toast.
Add enough liquid to be moist, but not too moist.
Cook in sprayed pan in 350° F. oven about 35 minutes or until done.

title: lasagne
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add meat and cook until crumbly.
Add tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes, remove from heat and let stand.
Skim off fat.
Beat eggs. Add cottage cheese, set aside.
Using a 9 x 13 inch pan, place thin layer of meat sauce, layer of noodles (4 or 5 strips); then layer of cottage cheese egg mixture.
Cover with half of mozzarella cheese, then 1/2 meat sauce, remaining noodles, rest of mozzarella cheese, rest of meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: company sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix well.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes more. Pierce top of cake with fork; pour topping onto cake.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: russian potato salad(for pastor and mike patterson)
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; peel and cut into cubes while still warm.
Add seasonings, Russian dressing and mayonnaise mixed with vinegar.
Chill.
Shortly before serving, add radishes and celery, adding more dressing if necessary.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into 12 biscuits.
Place on pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at about 400° until brown.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 300°.
While cake is warm, add frosting.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; place in bottom of dish.
A glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish is a good size pan to use.
Mix next 3 ingredients together with mixer and spread on top of pretzels.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Microwave on High.
Combine syrup and sugar in glass dish. Put in for 2 minutes.
Remove.
Add oleo and vanilla and stir until mixed.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Remove.
Stir in peanuts and microwave 2 minutes.
Stir in soda.
Pour on cookie sheet (buttered).

title: easy sausage bake
directions: Butter casserole good.
Break bread up and put in dish. Scramble sausage.
Drain.
Pour sausage over the bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over other ingredients.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with biscuit and jelly.

title: fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken, pulling off all visible fat; set aside.
Pour flour, garlic and pepper (enough for flavoring) into paper bag. Shake chicken in bag so that it is completely coated.
Fry at medium heat, using oil.
Sprinkle garlic and pepper for seasoning. Turn chicken over so that all sides are browned.
Fry approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: boiled brown cake(a holiday cake)
directions: Put first 10 ingredients in pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Set in pan of cold water if you wish. Dissolve 1 teaspoon of soda in warm water and stir into mixture and then gradually beat in 4 cups flour.
Put the walnuts in with last of flour.
Bake in a greased Bundt type pan for 1 hour at 350°. Let cool in pan and then turn out.

title: sugarless blueberry muffins
directions: Rinse and drain berries well and toss lightly with 2 teaspoons flour.
In large bowl, stir flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9-inch deep dish pie crust.
Put a regular 9-inch crust on top and press down.
Brown at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: crabmeat soup
directions: Combine and heat all ingredients except sherry.
Remove from heat and add sherry.

title: peanut butter whirls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, peanut butter, egg and vanilla. Alternate flour, salt and soda into mixture with 2 tablespoons milk.

title: chinese noodles
directions: Melt chips and add Chinese noodles; mix together.
Add peanuts; mix.
Put on wax paper.
Wait until cool to serve.

title: greek sesame seed candy
directions: Put the honey in a heavy saucepan and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Stir in the sesame seeds.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, for five minutes.
Pour a little orange water on a tray or marble board.
Tilt it several times so that the whole tray is moistened.
Pour on the honey mixture and spread it to a thickness of 1/2-inch.
Let the candy cool at room temperature.
Cut it into 1-inch squares.
Turn the pieces with a spatula and let them dry on a rack for 2 or 3 hours.
Store between layers of waxed paper in an airtight container.
Makes about 3 dozen pieces.

title: butter cookies(yields 5 to 6 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and add sugar, beating until creamy.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat.
Mix lemon juice and soda; add to mixture.
Add flour and mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Take 1/4 of dough and roll out on floured board.
Cut into shapes using cookie cutters.
Continue with remainder of dough.
Place cut-outs on cookie sheets and decorate with nuts and sprinkles.
Bake at 350° for a total of 8 minutes.
For more even baking, bake on bottom shelf for 4 minutes, rotate sheets and move to top shelf and bake remaining 4 minutes.
Cookies will not be brown.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix strawberry juice and cornstarch to make a glaze (2 cups). Cool and add berries.
Cut cake into slices and cut slices into fingers about half an inch wide.
Line the bottom and sides of a glass bowl with cake, leaving a small space between each.

title: chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all dry ingredients in large Ziploc bag.
Cut up fryer.
Shake chicken in bag to coat with seasonings. Arrange in baking pan (13 x 9-inch).
Pour water in bottom. Sprinkle with melted butter and oil.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Pour wine over chicken.
Lower heat to 325° and cover; bake 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 more minutes.

title: amaretto freeze
directions: Combine Amaretto and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves. Combine ice cream and Amaretto mixture in food processor; mix until smooth.
Pour into 6 parfait glasses and freeze.
Garnish with whipped cream and cherries.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy and gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust and chill 3 hours.
Top with strawberries and glaze. Refrigerate.

title: dad's carp bait
directions: Boil ingredients for 5 minutes.
Cool and store until ready to knead onto the hook.

title: dessert lime cooler
directions: Put all ingredients in the blender container.
Cover and set on blender until smooth.
Serve at once or place in the freezer or ice cube tray.
Makes 3 servings.

title: braised rabbit in wine sauce
directions: Roll rabbit pieces in flour.
Season with salt and pepper. In a large skillet saute rabbit pieces in 1/2 inch butter until well browned.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer over low heat until tender, about 1 hour.
(Add more water to sauce if necessary.)
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili-cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place cornbread dough on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press perforations together to seal, bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Stir together cream cheese, egg and cumin in a medium bowl until well blended.
Add cheese and chilies; mix well.
Spoon over crust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: cape may chowder(first prize winner)
directions: Drain clams; chop.
Do not run through grinder, that bruises them.
Do not add clam juice; it makes too strong a clam taste.

title: agression cookies
directions: Pile in a big bowl or on a clean, scrubbed counter.
Mash, squeeze and beat!
Mix well.
Form into walnut sized balls and flatten on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Freezes well for weeks.
You need to be real angry. Good for little kids or big kids.

title: favorite chicken casserole
directions: Spread chicken on bottom of a 2-quart
flat casserole dish. Dilute soup with milk.
Pour over chicken.
Cook celery and onion in broth until tender.
Combine broth, celery, onion, egg and stuffing.
Spread dressing on top of soup.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ranch burgers
directions: Mix ground chuck or round with dressing mix well.
Form into 4 patties and grill or broil until done.
Serve with your favorite burger trimmings.
Serves 4.

title: cracker jack corn puffs
directions: Bring butter, brown sugar and Karo to boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda and cook until it turns light brown. Pour over corn puffs and mix well to coat.

title: zucchini timbales
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat in eggs, cheese and ham. Place 1 teaspoon oil in each of four 6 ounce custard cups or individual souffle dishes.
Spoon mixture into each dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: ham loaf
directions: Moisten with a sprinkle of water and shape into 2 loaves. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Cover with foil before baking. Uncover after baking and pour a mixture of 1 can crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup brown sugar over both loaves. Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine soup, milk and mustard.
Add macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit filled tarts
directions: Flatten biscuits, dip in melted butter, then in cinnamon sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Make an indentation in the center of biscuit; fill with favorite fruit filling.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ann's yummy chicken pot pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper (garlic salt if desired). Pour in pie shell.
Turn second shell on top. Seal.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes (until golden brown).
Let sit 20 to 25 minutes before serving.

title: caramel icing
directions: Place 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet over low heat.
Mix in saucepan 2 cups sugar, milk, butter and egg.
Stir this mixture over low heat until butter melts.
Increase heat and cook until it boils rapidly.
When sugar in skillet is brown, pour it into the other boiling mixture, stirring fast and constantly.
Cook to soft-ball stage.
Add vanilla.
Boil to spreading consistency. Filling may be put on when thinner to soak into cake.

title: bavarian
directions: For crust, mix flour, margarine and pecans and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: missouri buttermilk pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg yolks and buttermilk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into other ingredients.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour into single unbaked crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour together, then add all remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick on medium heat.
Pour into prebaked pie shell and let cool.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place lemon juice over chicken.
Mix sour cream, celery soup and mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with Ritz crackers (about 2 dozen) crushed with 1 stick of margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Put back in oven and bake until brown.

title: peach cake delight(refreshing summer treat!)
directions: Yup, that's it.
Mix with hands on board or bowl.
Roll into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake in 325° oven on greased cookie sheet until lightly browned, about 8 to 12 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top (or a square of Hershey chocolate bar) and put a nut on top of soft chocolate.

title: cabbage for cabbage haters
directions: Slice cabbage.
Cook in salted water for 5 minutes.
Butter sides and base of casserole dish.
Put cabbage and 2 tablespoons butter in dish.
Add sugar, vinegar and sour cream.
Mix lightly. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Cream butter with sugars in large bowl until blended.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda in small bowl; stir into creamy mixture with oats, chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.
Drop onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Cut up chicken; brown quickly in hot oil.
Place in iron skillet.
Mix all the other ingredients up.
Pour mixture over browned chicken.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low.
Cook slowly, until real tender.
Cook with lid on.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain, squeeze as much liquid as possible by placing on paper towel.

Add broccoli buds (you may want to place the buds in salted water in case there are any unwanted varmits) for a few minutes, add onions and mix well with the mayonnaise. Refrigerate some time before serving.

title: nutty crust cherry glaze pie
directions: Add almonds to crust; bake and cool.
Add lemon juice and extracts to milk and mix until thick.
Fold in whipped cream.
Fil the crust and top with cherry filling formed as a ring.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces.
Combine 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon of cinnamon in plate or plastic bag.
Roll or shake each biscuit piece in sugar mixture.
Layer in a greased tube pan. Sprinkle remaining sugar over top.
Combine margarine, 1 cup sugar and 1/2 tablespoon of cinnamon in small saucepan; heat until boiling.
Pour over biscuits in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Loosen sides and invert on serving plate.
Serve hot.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine the dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients except the boiling water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in the boiling water.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch or three 8-inch cake pans or into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for the layers, 35 to 40 minutes for the 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
When cooled, remove from pans and frost with your favorite frosting.

title: texas cream of potato soup
directions: Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: good beef stew
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Coat beef pieces with flour.
Brown beef, a few pieces at a time, in oil in Dutch oven over medium heat; drain.
Remove beef from pan. Mix parsley, brown sugar, salt and rosemary in Dutch oven.
Stir in broth and vinegar gradually, scraping bottom of pan until gravy is smooth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in beer, onion, garlic and beef.
Add potatoes.
Cover and bake until beef and potatoes are tender, about 3 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lusitanian oysters(ostras lusitanas)
directions: Scrub oysters thoroughly; open slightly, then cook for a few minutes in a little water.
Reserve liquid and place oysters in a greased oven-safe dish.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine together.
Add oats, nuts and peanut butter.
Spoon onto waxed paper until cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare ground beef according to directions on seasoning mix package.
In a large salad bowl, combine lettuce, ground beef, olives, cheese, tomato, onion, garbanzo beans, avocado slices and broken nacho chips.
Serve with taco sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: poor man's frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk in saucepan until thick.
Cool until smooth.
Cream Crisco.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Then add cooled mixture.
Beat about 5 to 7 minutes until very creamy.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Remove bones and skin.
Combine seasoning and eggs, mixing well.
Add milk and flour; mix well.
Drop batter from tablespoon into hot oil; fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel. Makes 12 to 14 croquettes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: tex-mex appetizer pie
directions: Thaw frozen dip.
In separate bowl, combine sour cream, taco mix and mayonnaise.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove core of cabbage. Boil cabbage 5 minutes or until leaves are limp.

Remove from water. Drain and separate leaves, cutting off any hard stems. While leaves cool, mix remaining ingredients except tomato soup. Place 2 tablespoons meat mixture on 1 cabbage leaf and roll up; start at narrow end and tuck in both ends. Continue until all meat is used. Place side by side in 9 x 13 pan. Extra leaves can layer on bottom and top of cabbage rolls.
Dilute 3 cans soup with 2 cups of water. Pour over cabbage. Bake covered at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: homemade paint
directions: Dissolve soap in water and mix well with starch.
Add coloring.

title: walnut bread
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder, sugar and salt.
Sift together; add nuts.
Melt shortening and add to beaten egg and milk. Combine this mixture with dry ingredients, stirring only until blended.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate island
directions: Mix and sift first four ingredients.
Melt chocolate and butter; add to first mixture.
Combine milk and vanilla and blend into mixture.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix remaining sugar, brown sugar and cocoa and sprinkle over batter.
Pour coffee over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Very rich, but low-fat!

title: quick broccoli soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and bring to full boil over medium heat, stirring frequently to separate vegetables. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Garnish with lemon slice, if desired. Makes 3 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together pineapple and pie filling. Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Slice margarine and arrange on top of cake mix. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry.
Combine milk, salt, coconut and flavorings.
Mix thoroughly.
Carefully fold into egg whites.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-oiled baking sheet.
Bake in 325°
oven about 15 minutes.

title: carol's english muffins
directions: Brown sausage and crumble while frying; drain grease.
Melt cheese in pan with sausage.
After this is mixed together, split English muffins and spoon mixture on each muffin.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers with onions.
Add salt; let stand for 2 hours, then rinse in cold water and drain.
Heat vinegar, water, sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed, ginger and dill weed to boiling point.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Simmer for about 5 minutes or until cucumbers are greenish and somewhat translucent. Pack while hot into heated jars.

title: turkey au gratin casserole
directions: In medium-size bowl, whisk together salad dressing, oil and curry powder. Fold in apple, celery and turkey. Cover; refrigerate 30 minutes. Cut 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick lengthwise slice from each zucchini. Cut slices into "sticks" and save for snacking. Using melon baller or small spoon and starting from cut side, scoop out most of flesh from each zucchini, leaving a shell. Reserve the flesh for salad or other uses.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Layer in casserole, beginning and ending with coarse cracker crumbs.
Drizzle butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: date and nut-icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs, milk and vanilla together. Set aside. Sift flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder together. Add to creamy mixture. Mix well. Add cinnamon, dates and nuts. Mix. Make dough into rolls like "logs." Wrap in wax paper and chill. Take cookie dough out of refrigerator and slice. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 275° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In separate bowl, mix wet ingredients.
Pour together in one bowl and mix.
Roll into small balls and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Unwrap chocolate kisses and as soon as cookies come out of the oven, press 1 kiss down on each.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter and stir in brown sugar.
Cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Continue stirring, until boiling. Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in confectioners sugar and vanilla; beat with electric mixer until spreading consistency. Frosts 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and potato chips. Spread 1/2 mixture into a buttered casserole; sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese, then rest of the mixture.
Top with rest of cheese and crumbled chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate cheese and let stand at room temperature.
Add biscuit mix and sausage.
Roll in small balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: forgotten roast
directions: Place roast on a large piece of foil and arrange vegetables around it.
Sprinkle meat and vegetables with dry onion soup mix, then spoon undiluted mushroom soup on top.
Wrap loosely with foil, making sure it is sealed at top and sides.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set for 1/2 hour.
Drop by tablespoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: classic vegetable dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in small mixing bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Makes 2 cups.
Refrigerate.
It makes a plain baked potato a meal.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix the butter, soup, sour cream, onions and 2 cups Cheddar cheese, leaving one cup cheese for topping.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved 1 cup cheese over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crullers (liste)
directions: Beat yolks, salt, sugar, cream and liquor.
Add flour; knead dough until ready to roll out (let stand for 1/2 hour).
Add a little flour if needed to knead.

title: pizza easy - deep
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Mix Bisquick and water to form dough.
Pat into baking pan and up sides with floured hands.
Make a 3/4-inch rim on sides.
Cook and stir ground beef, bouillon cubes and garlic until beef is brown and cubes are dissolved.
Mix tomato sauce and oregano. Spread evenly over dough.
Spoon mixture evenly over sauce. Top with mushrooms, green pepper and cheese.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes. Crust will be tender.

title: empress spinach salad
directions: Cook and chop bacon; reserve bacon grease.
Wash spinach carefully several times to get rid of all sand, or buy prewashed and trimmed fresh spinach.
Give it a quick wash; dry well.
Place spinach in a bowl.
Add pimentos, bacon and eggs.
Combine oil and vinegar in second bowl.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, anchovies and lemon juice; mix well.
When ready to serve, discard bits of garlic.
Pour dressing and warm bacon grease together; stir until blended.
Pour over spinach; toss well and serve.
Serves 6.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine flour, egg and milk.
Cut onions into rings.
Dip in batter and fry in hot oil, turning once.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and eggs.
Beat for 5 minutes, or until smooth.
Add pineapple with juice and nuts.
Layer with vanilla wafers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Make the day before you need.

title: jerome cookies
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Melt margarine; add sugar.
Beat egg in evaporated milk and add to butter-sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add chopped nuts, coconut and cracker crumbs.
Spread on crackers in pan.
Put a layer of crackers on top.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes and slice crosswise having round slices. Place in a heavy saucepan. Add sugar, water and margarine.
Cook over low heat until potatoes are tender and liquid has made a light syrup.

title: mexican hamburger stew
directions: Mix the 3 cans of soup in large kettle.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and let simmer.
Brown meat with seasonings; add to soup mixture and simmer several minutes before serving over corn chips.

title: grape syrup
directions: Put grape and apple juice concentrate into a pan and bring to a boil.
Mix unbleached flour and water in a small bowl.
Add this to boiling mixture, stirring consistently for 2 minutes. Makes about 16 ounces.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour and measure, then sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time and beat after each one.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: strawberry fig preserve
directions: Sort and wash figs. Peel and put them in pot with strawberry Jell-O and sugar. Cook together until thick.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes or until tests done.

title: bacon hush puppies
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Remove bacon (save 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in skillet); drain bacon and crumble.
Set bacon and drippings aside.

title: salmon supreme
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid. Combine salmon with enough milk to make 1 1/2 cups. Beat egg yolks and combine with milk and salmon liquid. flake salmon. Fill buttered, 8-inch square baking pan with 1/2 of crumbs, then celery, flaked salmon and remaining crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika and melted butter. Evenly distribute milk-egg liquid and bake at 450° until top is golden, about 20 minutes. Beat egg white until stiff and fold in mayonnaise. Spread lightly and evenly over baked salmon. Return to oven and bake until golden brown, about 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate several hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in covered container, makes one quart.
Put 3 teaspoons in one cup hot water.

title: good snack
directions: Cut ham into strips.
Place one asparagus tip on ham strip. Roll up into jelly roll style.
Chill and ready to serve.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil, oranges and juice and cake mix.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cheese Pastry:
Let cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter soften at room temperature.
Blend with flour, then chill about 1 hour. Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place in tiny ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin tins.
Press dough on bottom and sides of tins.

title: chicken chinoise
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Heat oil to very hot in wok or large skillet.
Add chicken; cook 1 minute.
Add the vegetables and the ginger; cook 2 more minutes.
Add the chicken stock.
Mix the cornstarch with the water; add to the chicken, stirring constantly.
Add the soy sauce; cook 1 more minute. Serve over rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in hot water.
Blend mashed cranberry sauce with hot mixture.
Cool and add pecans, celery and apples. Chill until firm and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: no fail caramel icing
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan; let boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add powdered sugar, mixing until right texture for spreading on cake.
Add vanilla, if desired.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine pecans, cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar and set aside.
Blend flour, baking powder and soda.
Cream butter with remaining cup of sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with half of cinnamon-nut mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Top with remaining cinnamon-nut mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 9 servings.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill slightly and then beat until frothy.
Fold in the remaining ingredients.
Chill in mold until set.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts and dice.
Add to chopped celery, sweet relish and mayonnaise; salt to taste.
Can make sandwiches or put on crackers.

title: chili stew
directions: Mix all together.
Cook over medium-low heat, after it starts to boil, for 1 hour.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Make 1 (2 layer) cake; frost with white icing.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add bananas.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts. Mix well.
Makes two small loaves.
Put in greased pans and bake 1 hour at 300° to 325°.
Frost with plain icing if desired.

title: decorating frosting
directions: Mix shortening with 2 cups powdered sugar.
Cream until smooth.
Add egg white (unbeaten), flavoring and salt.
Add the 2 remaining cups of powdered sugar and mix until well beaten.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix until well blended.
Chill.
Very good.
(Can also use 3/4 cup Italian dressing and 3/4 cup Miracle Whip.) Vegetables should total 3 cups.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix 2 beaten eggs and flour together.
Add sugar and undrained pineapple.
Put into 8-inch casserole.
Melt butter or oleo.
Add 4 to 6 slices of cubed bread (not over heat); let bread absorb butter.
(If necessary, add more bread.)
Place this over casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place raw rice in bottom of casserole. Brown pork chops in hot skillet. Place pork chops on top of rice.
Arrange slices of tomato, onion and pepper rings on top of each pork chop.
Pour can of chicken broth over this. Bake in 375° oven for about 1 hour.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast
in warm water and add remaining ingredients. Mix
well.
Roll
out
on
floured board 1/4-inch thick. Cut and dip in melted butter.
Let rise one hour.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: seed cookies
directions: Cream shortening, white and brown sugars together.
Add eggs to mixture and blend well.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine sour milk with vanilla.
Alternately add flour and milk to shortening mixture and blend all.
Shape cookie by hand into little logs and roll in sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed.
Add flour, wheat germ, sugar, cinnamon and baking soda to combine.
Then at high speed, mix thoroughly.
Fold in nuts.

title: camper's hash
directions: Saute diced pepper, onions and bacon in a large skillet until transparent.
Add the hamburger and cook until no pink shows. Combine the remaining ingredients and set aside.
To the hamburger, add 4 cups of diced potatoes and simmer until liquid is evaporated (about 15 minutes).
Some of the grease from burger can be drained before you add the catsup mixture, if you like.

title: lime punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add sugar and stir to dissolve. Add other ingredients in order. Serve cold. An ice ring does better in cooling the punch without diluting too much. Yields approximately 4 1/2 quarts.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough roll into 1/8-inch slices.
Put on pizza pan. (Do not overlap.)
Bake as on directions.
Cool.

title: spinach mushroom burrito
directions: Saute mushrooms in oil.
Add a little water and steam; add salt and pepper.
Place spinach on open tortilla; add mushrooms and cheese.
Broil in toaster oven about 2 minutes until spinach wilts and cheese melts.
Fold tortilla burrito-fashion and serve with sour cream and Oasis salsa.

title: wassail cup
directions: Combine apple cider and brandy or apple jack in a large saucepan.
Stir in sugar; add cloves and cinnamon.
Heat over low heat until just warm.
Transfer to a punch bowl.
Float apple and lemon slices on top.

title: frozen strawberry banana salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese with sugar.
Add strawberries while softened, but not completely thawed.
Add remaining fruit and whipped topping; mix well.
Pour into a loaf pan and freeze. Slice and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute onion and margarine for 10 minutes.
Boil broccoli in separate pan.
Put rest of ingredients in pan with onion and margarine. Stir frequently.
Put broccoli in medium casserole and pour sauce over.
Stir well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes until crispy brown on top.

title: anise toast
directions: Beat eggs and sugar 5 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix flour and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture. Add in juice and mix until thick.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour out onto cookie sheet in 2 strips (remember, mixture is very thick).
Bake 20 minutes at 375°. Slice into 1-inch strips.
Turn on cookie sheet and toast under broiler.
Turn over and toast on other side.

title: fantasy cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Cream butter, cream cheese and then mix in 1 egg at a time.
Stir in sugar and mix.
Stir in flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix good until creamy.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean and golden brown.

title: potato-beef casserole
directions: Takes 2 1/2 hours to prepare and cook.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Cover. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: chilled pasta with spicy peanut sauce
directions: *Or 2 tablespoons hot sesame oil and 2 tablespoons plain, pure sesame oil.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions, mixing two layers. Let cool and slice layers in half.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut and spread between layers.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sides of cake.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with oat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: amber's favorite lasagna
directions: Boil noodles.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Add sauce.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white fudge cake
directions: Mix.
Grease an oblong pan and bake at 300° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and put icing on it.

title: duck braised
directions: Season the duck; melt butter in large skillet.
Flour duck and fry until brown on each side.
Remove from pan and cook onion and celery in drippings until tender.
Return duck to pan and add cream.
Cover.
Cook over low heat about 1 hour or until tender.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat margarine in a large saucepan until melted, over low heat.
Add flour, mustard, salt, onion powder and white pepper. Cook until bubbly, about 1 minute, stirring constantly with wire whisk.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Stir in macaroni.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes before serving. Serves 12.

title: patties with gravy
directions: Soak roll or bread slices in water.
Soak out excess water and mix well with hamburger, onion, egg, nutmeg, salt and pepper. Shape into round patties approximately 2 1/2-inches in diameter. Brown both sides in hot shortening.
Set patties on platter and drain grease.
Add gravy mix and water to pan and cook and stir until thickened.
Add patties and simmer 15 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

To bake, roll dough to about 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter or drop by spoon onto baking sheet that has been sprayed lightly with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough can be stored in the refrigerator and used as needed.

title: lite shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute vegetables and herbs in olive oil until onion is clear. Brown flour (see roux recipe) and add to vegetables.
Slowly add water, mixing well, until thoroughly combined.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp, and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until they turn pink.
Adjust seasoning if necessary. Serve with rice.

title: barbecue sauerkraut
directions: In frypan, combine all ingredients with 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Cook over low heat until all liquid has evaporated. Serve at room temperature.

title: orange-walnut salad
directions: Tear or chop lettuce and spinach; add oranges and onion.
In a small saucepan, saute walnuts in oleo; add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cool a little and pour over salad and toss.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Add applesauce. Then add flour, nutmeg, allspice, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add chopped nuts.
Blend well.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Brush bread on both sides with 1 tablespoon of the oil.
Place on a baking sheet; bake until toasted, about 5 minutes per side.
Rub cut sides of garlic over both sides of bread.
Cut toasted bread into 1/2-inch croutons. Place lettuce in a large salad bowl.
Top with croutons, ham, eggs and tomatoes.
In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine lemon juice, anchovy paste, salt and pepper.
Shake to blend.
Add the remaining oil; shake again until well mixed.
Pour dressing over salad; toss gently.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Flake shrimp.
Mix all ingredients.
Top with cocktail sauce, if desired.
Serve on crackers.

title: sour cream sauce for cucumbers
directions: Blend shredded cucumber with other ingredients and chill. (Good with sliced cucumbers and onions.)

title: crab louis and pasta
directions: Prepare salad as directed on box; except stir in chili sauce with mayonnaise.
Stir green onion, bell pepper and crabmeat into finished salad.
Just before serving, stir in 2 cups of lettuce. Place remaining 2 cups lettuce on platter; arrange salad over lettuce.
Arrange tomato wedges around salad.

title: greek sauce
directions: Brown beef, drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours uncovered.
If hotter sauce is desired, add more pepper flakes.

title: pat's asparagus aspic
directions: Boil together for 3 minutes the sugar, vinegar, 1 cup water and salt.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water and add to boiled mixture.
Cool until syrupy.
While cooling, mix remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: apple omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix eggs and applesauce. Beat really good. Put in buttered casserole dish. Top with salt, pats of butter and cinnamon. Bake for 1 hour.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Scald and cool milk and shortening.
Mix yeast, water and some sugar in pan; let rise.
Add eggs and rest of sugar to yeast mixture, then pour in milk and shortening mixture.
Add flour; stir well.
Put in refrigerator to cool and rise.
It can be used some hours later, but better to leave in refrigerator overnight.
Form in circle (like 8-slice pie).
Roll from the outside to the center. Put on pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: low calorie banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat until fluffy.
Prepare in a dish:
1 layer of vanilla wafers, 1 layer of bananas, 1 layer of custard.
Repeat until all is gone.
Refrigerate.

title: plum coffee bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add food coloring and plums.
Mix well.
Sift in dry ingredients and blend.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes in preheated 325° oven.
Turn out on rack to cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: parsley rice pilaf
directions: Bring broth, water, salt and butter to a boil. Add rice. Cover and reduce heat to simmer. Cook until all liquid is absorbed. Stir in parsley and almonds.

title: cheesecake
directions: Lay out cream cheese to soften.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip until smooth.
Layer bottom of graham cracker crust with sliced banana.
Pour cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture on top of banana.
Lay sliced pineapple on top.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: crumb-coated chicken(for microwave)
directions: In small bowl beat together eggs, butter and salt.
Place cracker crumbs in shallow baking dish.
Coat chicken with cracker crumbs, then egg mixture, then cracker crumbs again.
In 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish arrange chicken with the meatier pieces to the outside edge of dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at high 18 to 22 minutes. Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 10 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.

title: golden date cake
directions: Mix flour, granulated sugar, milk, Crisco and vanilla extract 2 minutes on medium.
Add eggs and dates.
Beat 2 minutes and fold in nuts.
Bake in 2 layers for 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven. Cool.
Frost with Orange Icing.

title: tuna-chicken salad
directions: Mix well.
Low fat mayonnaise or dressing will save calories and fat grams.
Great for sandwiches or served with crackers.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until mixture is like corn meal.
Add milk and egg to form a soft dough. Drop by teaspoon into boiling broth.
Cover tightly and cook for 12 minutes without removing lid.
Serve.

title: crispy butternut chicken
directions: Chop peanuts finely in blender or food processor.
Combine with cornflake crumbs on a piece of waxed paper.
Pour salad dressing into pie plate.

Remove skin from chicken and dip each piece in salad dressing, then roll in crumb mixture to coat. Arrange chicken on microwave meat or bacon rack, thick pieces toward the outside, thinner or bony pieces toward the center. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes, rotating rack midway through cooking.
Let stand for 5 minutes before eating, or cool slightly and refrigerate if transporting to a picnic!

title: cranberry freeze
directions: Soften cheese; blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream to which powdered sugar and vanilla have been added.
Pour into loaf pan and freeze at least 6 hours.

title: candied sweet potatoes(from gertrude hart's recipe file)
directions: Peel raw potatoes and slice.
Combine butter, sugar and water in skillet.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour, turning often.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, combine Marshmallow Creme, sugar, milk, butter and salt; bring to full boil, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add semi-sweet morsels; stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into foil lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: no peek beef
directions: Put beef in 3-quart casserole.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in 325° oven for 3 hours. Do not peek.
Serve with rice, noodles or diced potatoes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine ingredients in a large glass or crockery bowl and chill overnight.
Serve soup cold with a dollop of sour cream on top of each serving.
Serve with croutons.
Hint: Serve in chilled bowls.
Serves 8.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice; take pineapple juice and add water to make 2 cups.
Bring to boil.
Add jello and marshmallows.
Add ingredients.
When cool, put in molds or cut in blocks and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: whole wheat onion bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Dust lightly with flour.

title: texas lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic until meat is thoroughly brown; drain.
To meat, add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Cook frozen spinach according to package directions.
(Do not season.) Drain.
Cook shell macaroni until soft; drain.
Mix together bread crumbs, eggs and salad oil.
In a mixing bowl, mix together spinach, macaroni and bread and egg mixture.
In a lightly greased oblong (9 x 13-inch) casserole dish, spread spinach and macaroni mixture.
Spread meat sauce on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with shredded cheese and let stand until cheese melts.
Serve with fresh salad and garlic bread.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water.
Add to all other ingredients and then flour.
Place in oiled bowl and let rise double.
You can make out the biscuits or refrigerate until needed.
Dough will keep in refrigerator 2 days.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and molasses. Stir in dry ingredients. Chill for an hour. Roll into small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Makes about 9 dozen.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Serve with favorite fresh vegetables.
You'll want to double this recipe often.
It disappears quickly.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in double boiler.
Cool. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake very slow in preheated (300° to 325°) oven 20 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pie cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in an extra large sheet pan or deep cookie sheet pan.
Done when cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool completely.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Chill completely.
Spread over top of cake evenly.
Then spread pie mix over top of pudding mix.
Refrigerate immediately.

title: just for kids muddley dough
directions: Mix well and knead.
Texture will be very grainy.
Store in an airtight container.

title: simple shrimp spread
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add shrimp and onion; blend well.
Add a few drops Tabasco sauce to taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and celery in large skillet.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add both cans of beans and tomatoes.
Simmer for 20 minutes, adding water as needed.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a boil and slowly stir grits into it.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Over low heat, stir in cheese and oleo until melted.
Set off heat and stir in well beaten eggs and Tabasco sauce.
Bake in buttered casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: speedy pineapple cheese cake(dietetic)
directions: Empty the canned crushed pineapple into a strainer over a cup to catch the juice.
Press the pineapple to eliminate as much moisture as possible.
Spread the well drained pineapple in the bottom of the ready to fill pie shell.
Sprinkle the gelatin in 2 tablespoons cold water in the bottom of the blender container. Wait until gelatin dissolves and softens.
Measure pineapple juice and add water to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling.
Add boiling juice mixture to gelatin.
Cover and blend on high speed until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Cut cream cheese into chunks and add to blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add vanilla yogurt and vanilla.
Cover and blend smooth.
Spoon into the pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Chill until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Trim crusts from bread and fit into bottom of dish.
Distribute sausage over bread.
Place eggs, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and milk in blender and blend well.
Spread cheeses over sausage and cover with milk mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and allow to sit in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Soft textured bread should not be used.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat together the corn oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, about 1/3 at a time, blending well after each addition.
Stir in prunes and nuts.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Cream together the sour cream, cream cheese, green chillies, black olives, garlic powder and grated cheese.
Divide the mixture on the 10 flour tortillas; spread evenly.
Roll up the tortillas and cut in approximately 1-inch pieces.
Set in a low dish; cool for several hours.
Serve with salsa (mild, medium or hot) or picante sauce (to be used as a dipping sauce).

title: party punch
directions: Slightly defrost strawberries and oranges; mix with prepared orange juice.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Add well chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Add orange slices if desired.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Stir only until particles are moistened.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: german chocolate style brownies
directions: Bake brownies as directed on package (cake like).
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk, egg yolks and shortening.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans. Cool 15 minutes.
Spread over brownies.

title: easiest roast ever
directions: Put roast in middle of a large sheet of heavy foil. Mix other 4 ingredients together and pour over roast. Seal roast in foil leaving little space. Cook 3 to 4 hours in a 350° oven.

title: tiny quiche tarts
directions: Cut pastry into 2-inch circle and gently line small muffin tins.
Into pastry shell sprinkle small amount of chopped onion. Sprinkle small amount of crumbled bacon.

title: mexican cream cheese burritos
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; spread on each tortilla.
Roll tightly.
Place seam side down.
Chill for several hours.
Cut off roll ends.
Cut into slices, about 1-inch.
Makes about 40.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind and mix squash, onion, green pepper and pimento.
Soak in salt overnight.
Drain.
Add other ingredients; boil 5 minutes, then simmer 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal hot.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown
ground
chuck, onion and garlic juice.
Pour off fat. Stir
in
spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer about 20 minutes. Stir
in cottage
cheese.
Cook noodles until tender.
Drain. Arrange layers of noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: lemon bonbons
directions: Mix butter and sugar until very light and fluffy.
Add cornstarch and flour, mixing well.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on nuts scattered on wax paper.
Flatten with bottom of glass, dipped in flour.
With spatula, place cookies on ungreased cookie sheet, nut side up.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool and frost with Bonbon Frosting.

title: beef balls with gravy
directions: Combine meat, milk, crumbs, onion and salt.
Shape into 18 balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown on all sides in shortening.
Mix soup and water in casserole dish.
Put the drained meat balls in the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown on top.

title: party crab potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
