Put in buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Potatoes should be fairly stiff before adding sour cream or they are too runny.
Great with steaks.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Combine the ingredients in a large bowl and mix with dressing.

title: secret cake recipe (red cake)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and eggs. Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring; add this to shortening mixture; add salt and buttermilk with flour; and vanilla, vinegar and soda.
Do not beat hard, just blend in.
Bake at 350.
Let cool and split layers through the center, then frost this scarlet creation.

title: butter pecan balls
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter, mixing well after each addition. Stir in nuts and then flour, 1/3 cup at a time.
Chill dough until stiff enough to handle, about 2 or 3 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brightly brown on bottom.
Place on wire rack to cool. Roll in xxx sugar and then again. Makes 4 dozen.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in small amount fat over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until rice is done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook all ingredients except peanut butter, vanilla and butter. Boil on medium heat until reaches soft ball stage, then put rest of ingredients in immediately and pour into an 8 x 11-inch pan. Do not refrigerate.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cook elbows, drain.
Sprinkle chops with salt, brown them in a skillet.
Combine elbows and remaining ingredients and turn into a casserole, lay chops on top.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350° for 40 minutes or until chops are tender; or cook chops until almost tender and then place on top and bake for only 25 minutes.

title: macaroons
directions: Soften sherbet in bowl.
Add cake mix and extract.
Blend until well mixed.
Stir in coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: renya's tex mex salad
directions: Mix corn and dressing and just before serving, add Fritos.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Sprinkle coconut and broken pecans in pan. Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box. Pour over coconut and pecans. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine. Drop by spoonfuls over top of cake in pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Check. Put foil under cake because the top runs over a little.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Stir in cream and cook slowly, until mixture thickens.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks and gradually return to hot mixture.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Add sherry, lemon juice, salt and parsley. Serves 4 each 5-inch patty shells.
"A gourmet delight."

title: fantasy fudge(very rich)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in heavy 5-quart Dutch oven. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Pour into two 13 x 9-inch baking pans.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Add two cups salt to 1 gallon of water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand for 7 days.
Rinse well.
Pour clear boiling water over cucumbers.
Let stand for 1 day; drain.
Pour boiling alum water over cucumbers.
Use four or five tablespoons alum.
Let stand for one day.
The next day, soak in clear boiling water.
Make syrup (sugar, vinegar, allspice), boil and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand one day.
The next day, boil again.
Put in jars.
Boil juice down just enough to cover pickles.

title: stuffed shells florentine
directions: Boil shells until flexible.
Mix first 7 ingredients and then stuff this mixture into shells.
Spread Prego or Ragu on bottom of saucepan. Put stuffed shells in and pour rest of Prego over stuffed shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and Mozzarella prior to cooking at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Cook broccoli only enough to thaw; drain well.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat baking mix with milk and eggs until smooth.
Slowly pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: layered butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.

title: beef and carrot soup
directions: Brown beef, garlic and onion.
Drain off fat.
Put remaining ingredients in kettle and boil.
Turn down heat; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add meat mixture.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: parmesan-garlic cheese spread
directions: Beat all ingredients until creamy.
Put in a nonmetal container. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Makes 2 cups and stores for 2 weeks.
Serve on toasted French bread.

title: french onion soup(serves 6)
directions: Combine margarine and onions.
Cover and cook slowly about 15 minutes.
Blend in salt and flour.
Add beef broth or stock.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer about 1 hour.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Slice ice cream and put between two layers of waffles.
Serve on warm day with napkins to 1 kid.
Multiples of each can be made with this recipe.
Yummy.

title: jew bread
directions: Cook eggs and brown sugar on low heat until warm to touch. Set aside to cool.
Add flour, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into cookie sheet which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice into squares.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Add flour mixture.
Flour and grease bundt pan.
Pour mixture in pan and bake at 350 for 50 minutes or until done.

title: sue's vegetable beef soup
directions: Place raw vegetables in large micro-proof bowl.
Season with dash of onion salt, garlic powder and plenty of good fresh ground pepper.
Add 1/3 cup water.
Cover and microwave on High until just tender.
Crumble beef in a large pot over Medium-high heat. Sprinkle with chili powder until surface is well dusted.
Add onion and saute until meat is browned.
Add canned and fresh vegetables, including water and other vegetable broths.
Soup should appear thinner than you like to eat it.
Add seasonings to taste.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat and simmer until either:
(a) the ball game is over, (b) the house is clean, (c) the Sunday crossword puzzle is complete (2 to 3 hours), stirring occasionally.

title: tracie's chocolate chip cake(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Mix ingredients together. Bake at 325° for 1 hour in greased Bundt cake pan. When cake has cooled, sift confectioners sugar over top. Delicious!

title: casey creek jam cake
directions: Cream butter and add sifted brown sugar.
Beat egg yolks separately and add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Add jam. Flour the nuts and raisins with 1/4 cup of the flour.
Add cocoa, cinnamon and cloves to the remaining flour and sift again. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with flour mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Add floured raisins and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Grease a 9-inch tube pan and bake at 250° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sin (nut goodie bar)
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients.
Put 1/2 mixture in a buttered 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add dry roasted peanuts to remaining mixture.
Stir and set aside.
Melt butter or margarine, pudding and milk.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat. Add powdered sugar and maple flavoring.
Mix until smooth.
Spread over mixture in pan and cool in refrigerator.
Spread nut mixture on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: old-fashioned baked lemon pudding
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Beat egg yolks; mix well with remaining ingredients.
Beat into egg whites at slow speed.
Bake in greased dish or custard dishes set in hot water.
Have water as deep as sauce is desired.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
When ready to serve, add 2 bottles ginger ale.
Add food color if desired.
Serves 50.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Saute onion and garlic in a little butter until limp.
Combine onion mixture with artichokes and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: frozen lime mint salad
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, dry lime Jell-O, marshmallows and mints.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or until marshmallows begin to melt.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into paper cupcake holders in muffin pans and freeze.
Top with a red cherry for some added color.

title: cream of asparagus soup salad
directions: Heat soup (undiluted); dissolve jello in it.
Add cream cheese, then add other ingredients.
Blend well and pour into shallow pan or mold.

title: potatoes in blue
directions: Wash potatoes; remove a "ring" of peeling from center of each. Leave remaining peel.
In a saucepan, boil potatoes in enough water to cover potatoes.
Cook until done but still firm.
Drain water.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Mix vegetables, sour cream, soup, half onions and half cheese in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and cup up, heat oil and add chopped onion, mushrooms, tomatoes, pepper and highly seasoned chicken.
Put spaghetti in boiling salted water, cook fifteen minutes.
Blanch and add grated cheese.
Mix with other ingredients, then bake in 300 degree oven about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-kiwi cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.

title: maple butterscotch brownies
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and maple flavoring.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cool; dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pack whole beans in pint jars.
Add the first 3 ingredients. Heat the vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to a boil and add to jars.
Makes about 4 pints.

title: yaka soba
directions: Stir-fry celery, carrots, onions and green peppers until tender-crisp.
If using fresh green beans, they should also be added with these ingredients.
(Approximate cooking time is 1 hour.)
Add cabbage and mushrooms (and canned green beans) and cook, covered, for about 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Add the bite-size pieces of browned crisp bacon.
Serve stir-fry over rice with soy sauce to taste.

title: apricot flip
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in mixing the bowl 1/2 cup margarine or butter, sugar, scalded milk and salt.
Stir to melt butter or margarine to lukewarm.
Add unbeaten eggs, beating after each.
Gradually add flour to form stiff ball of dough. Knead for 5 minutes on floured surface.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger and onion until done, then add seasoning, garlic, sauce, paste and mushrooms.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Put layer of noodles and half of sauce.
Sprinkle some Parmesan cheese and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers. Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: cheesy mexican rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until onion is clear.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in deep casserole dish for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: one pan chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chicken.
Lay cut up chicken on top of mixture.
Cover and bake slowly at 350° for 3 hours.

title: strawberry pie(nine-inch)
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients until thick.
Stir constantly.
Let cool.
Bake pie shell.
Put strawberries in pie shell and cover with filling.
Smooth Cool Whip over filling.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in bowl and mix in dry jello.
Drain pineapple and add to cottage cheese and jello.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put in serving bowl and chill.

title: cheddar pecan toasts
directions: In
a bowl, cream together cheese, butter, sherry, salt and Tabasco.
Stir
in pecans. Spread on pita and broil 1 to 2 minutes.

title: banana crush
directions: Combine banana and juices in blender.
Mix well.
Add crushed ice gradually.
Process until thickened.
Pour into glass.
Serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend in cream and seasonings.
Stir in shrimp and add paprika as desired for color.
Serve with sturdy potato chips or other "dippers".
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line dish with whole crackers.
Whip pudding as directed on box.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer crackers and mixture until all is used.
Will be about 3 layers with crackers on top.
Cover with chocolate icing.

title: watermelon salad
directions: Pour over chunks of any of the following:
bananas, watermelon, cantaloupe, blueberries, honeydew, strawberries, peaches and grapes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, eggs, pineapple and pecans in bowl.
Stir until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients in order as listed.
Chill for 2 hours.
Best served with Wheatables crackers.

title: potatoes for everyone
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a large casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly and heated through or cook in microwave for 10 minutes on High.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cheese crescents
directions: Mix flour and butter until dough forms.
Chill in freezer for 10 minutes.
Divide in thirds.
Roll each third into 10-inch circle.
Cut each circle into 10 wedge shaped pieces.
Spread with farmer cheese which has been mixed with the egg and salt.
Roll as for croissants.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Combine and shake ingredients.
Pour over peeled tomatoes. Small tomatoes make a lovely dish.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl mix 1 1/2 cups flour with sugar, salt and yeast. Heat water and butter to
125° (hot to the touch), mix with the dry ingredients.
Add egg and remaining flour to make soft dough. Cover bowl and let	dough
rise 1 hour.
Knead on floured surface until smooth.
Roll
out
dough
and
cut your rolls out.
Put rolls in baking dish or pan (oil baking pan or dish).
Rolls should be turned in the oil.
Let rise 1 hour or until double in size.
Makes about 20 rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: taco dip spread
directions: Add taco seasoning and water to browned hamburger. Mix and remove from heat. Spread cream cheese in bottom and sides of baking dish or pan. Pour hamburger mixture over cream cheese. Sprinkle diced onion and diced tomato on top of hamburger. Spread salsa over other ingredients. Sprinkle with Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 400° until cheese melts and browns on top.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla, milk and peanut butter.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Blend into other mixture.
Shape into walnut size balls and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Take from oven and place a Hershey Kiss on top of each cookie.
Press down a little and bake 2 minutes more.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: salsa grilled chicken
directions: Place thawed chicken breast on medium-hot grill for 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until juices run clear when filet is pricked.
Remove from grill.
Keep hot.

title: state fair oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Let stand for 1 hour. Thoroughly cream together shortening and brown and white sugars. Sift flour, soda and cinnamon into sugar mixture.
Mix well. Blend in eggs and raisins, oatmeal and nuts.
(Dough will be stiff.)
May need to blend with hands.
Push dough from heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten between hands and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Do not overbake.

title: karo icebox christmas cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat butter until soft and creamy.
Add Karo syrup and sugar.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly with hands until stiff dough is formed.
Shape into 3 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper; chill in refrigerator 3 or 4 hours or until firm enough to slice.
Slice about 1/8-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: trout with caper sauce
directions: Combine salt, pepper and flour in shallow dish.
Pour milk into another shallow dish.
Heat about 3 tablespoons olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Dip fillets, one at a time into milk and then flour mixture and coat well.
Cook fillets until light brown and cooked through (about two minutes on each side). Transfer to warming platter.

title: dessert bread rolls
directions: Mix the cream cheese, 1/2 cup of sugar, egg yolk and lemon juice with an electric mixer until smooth.
Cut crust from bread slices and roll out bread with rolling pin.
Spread bread slices with cream cheese mixture and roll up.
Melt butter.
Mix cinnamon and 1 cup of sugar.
Dip bread rolls in melted butter and then in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place rolls on cookie sheet covered with waxed paper.
Freeze.
When ready to bake, cut rolls in half. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: smoked turkey supreme
directions: Combine salt and oil in a two cup measuring cup.
Using about 1/4 cup of the salt paste, rub the mixture
over the large and wishbone cavities.
To the remaining salt paste, add the vinegar, pepper and parsley.

Place turkey in a water smoker (or if using other type of hooded grill, place a large water pan in the cooking unit) and smoke with hickory or apple wood 5 to 6 hours, depending on the size of the bird.
While the bird smokes, baste with the sauce liberally every hour or so.
The turkey will be nut brown with a tasty crust and moist inside.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Thoroughly mix together the butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Then stir in the flour, salt and nuts.
Chill dough. Then roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake until set, but not brown at 400°, for 10 to 12 minutes.
While still warm, roll ball in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar again. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: christmas special fruitcake
directions: Add nuts, raisins and cherries to flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir until nuts and cherries are well coated.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in nut mixture.
Pour into greased and floured wax paper lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Turn on rack to cool.

title: snappy strudel
directions: Mix together like pie crust the flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture and add 1 teaspoon cinnamon to it.
To the rest of the mixture, add egg, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and buttermilk.
Mix well and put in 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle cup of reserved mixture over top. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Melt margarine; add onion, bell pepper and saute 15 or 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add flour, cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add parsley and crawfish tails; cook covered 15 to 20 minutes.
Add half and half, Velveeta cheese and garlic; cover and cook on low 30 minutes.
Cook fettucine; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Combine fettucine and crawfish mixture and pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hilltop favorites
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Set this aside.
Cream softened margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat.
Blend in flour mixture, then oatmeal.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at about 375° for about 10 minutes.
Watch carefully to avoid overbaking.
Makes up to 6 dozen small cookies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese). Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Pour in mixture.
Spread sour cream on top.
Sprinkle cheese on sour cream.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes, until middle is set.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup, salt and water together until a hard ball is formed in water or until 263° to 265° is reached. Remove from fire and pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites. Add nuts, candied cherries (cut in small pieces) and vanilla.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss and will hold shape when dropped from the spoon.
Drop onto buttered cookie sheet from spoon.

title: smoked sausage stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add broccoli, pepper, celery, carrots and onion.
Stir-fry over moderately high heat for 4 minutes.
Add sausage, tomato and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 7 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: scalloped cabbage(freda adams - bethel, ohio)
directions: Drop cabbage into boiling water and boil until barely tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Put half of the cabbage in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, spreading evenly.
Top with remaining cabbage, onion, sugar, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese, then bread crumbs.
Pour the milk evenly over all.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 14 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vanilla wafer tarts
directions: Place 1 wafer in foil baking cups.
Fill about 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture (cream cheese, eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice).
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top with pie filling.

title: wassail
directions: Mix juice, sugar and cider in the biggest pot you have.
Put spices in a cheesecloth and simmer in the covered pot.

title: calico tuna rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook rice according to directions.
In a casserole dish, combine soup and milk, tuna, vegetables, and cooked rice.
Gently stir mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: grandma's molasses banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; beat in egg, molasses and banana.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: hot cheesy-beef dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
Melt cheese in crock-pot, adding tomatoes and mushroom soup (and peppers, if desired) as cheese melts.
Add cooked meat and onion.
(Be sure the meat is drained well when you finish frying.) Keep warm with medium heat in crock-pot.

title: punch
directions: Mix in 10-quart kettle. Mix well and enjoy.
Put in punch bowl.
Place sherbet on top of ingredients after adding to bowl. Also can garnish with slices of orange or lemon.
Frozen juice ring you make up before.
This makes 1 batch, serves 20 people.

title: microwave peanut or pecan brittle
directions: Stir syrup and sugar together.
Cook on High for 4 minutes. Add peanuts or pecans, stir and cook on High 3 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla and magarine.
Add baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour on buttered sheet pan.
Spread.
Do not use spoon to spread.

title: chicken with wine
directions: Brush chicken lightly with oil; salt and pepper chicken. Place in casserole dish and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Pour wine over dish and bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Pour mushroom slices and mushroom soup over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: overnight puff cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Put into oven and turn oven off.
Leave overnight or at least 5 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, vanilla and juice. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spoonburgers
directions: In skillet, brown meat over medium heat.
Drain.
Add garlic, onion and salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Spoon onto toasted buns.
Yield:
8 sandwiches.

title: mexican cheese rolls
directions: Combine ingredients in food processor.
Spread creamed ingredients on flour tortillas and roll jelly roll style. Refrigerate rolls for 2 hours.
Cut rolls into sections and serve.

title: torte cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease and flour 4 round pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or less.
Watch.
Cool.

title: mom's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar in small mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well until light and fluffy.
Transfer to large bowl.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add soda to buttermilk and add alternately to the butter and sugar mixture, beating after each addition.
Add jam and beat.
Add raisins, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) cake pans at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove tops and seeds from peppers. Blanch in boiling water for 4 minutes.
Drain; set aside.
Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onion and rice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix in 1/2 can of soup.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Stand in glass dish for baking.
Mix remaining soup with 1/2 soup can of water.
Pour over peppers in dish and cover.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: raw apple bread
directions: Mix the flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Blend in flour mixture.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Mix 3 tablespoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon; sprinkle over top of dough.
Bake at 350° for approximately 60 minutes or until done.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Crumble uncooked ground beef in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion.
Cover beef with cheese.
Add green beans.
Spread soup over beans.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey-peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, honey, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs until smooth and creamy.
Add dry ingredients until mixed. Dough will not be stiff.
Mix in cut up peanut butter cups and chips.
Refrigerate dough 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.
Mmmm goood!

title: quickie blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder, milk and vanilla; pour into baking dish over margarine.
Pour blueberries over mixture; press blueberries down. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spring garden salad
directions: Combine in small saucepan and marinate first 6 ingredients. Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool. In a large bowl, combine the last 7 ingredients.
Pour in marinade and stir.
Cover and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: grandma's fabric stiffener
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Dip fabric or lace in solution. Arrange material and shape on wax paper.
Dry thoroughly.

title: pepper salad
directions: Bake peppers in hot (450°) oven for about 20 minutes, or until wilted and soft.
Remove seeds and outer skin.
Cut in pieces; place in a bowl.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Mix vinegar and olive oil; add to peppers.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Adjust seasonings, if necessary.
Serve as an appetizer, or just with fresh Italian bread.
Serves 12.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix lemon juice in milk thoroughly.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: italian hot dogs
directions: Saute bell peppers and onions (sliced thin) in olive oil (brown).
Saute potatoes (sliced thin) until cooked.
Set aside. Slice hot dogs lengthwise and brown on both sides without grease. Mix all ingredients; add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Serve hot on hot dog buns.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie crust for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.
Melt Hershey bars in saucepan on low heat.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve cold with ice cream or Cool Whip or just enjoy plain.

title: easy bake cheesecake
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Chill before serving.
Garnish with your favorite fruit topping.
Serves 8.

title: acorn squash bake
directions: Clean
squash and cut in half.	Turn halves upside down in pan of water.
Place butter in each half.
Sprinkle vanilla,
then sugar,
on each and top with a pinch of cinnamon on each.	Bake about
10 minutes upright at 350°.	Makes 2 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add fruit cocktail, egg and 1 stick melted butter or margarine.
Mix about 30 seconds.
Don't overmix.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Take from oven and pour 1/4 stick melted margarine or butter over cake.

title: fruit lovers delight
directions: Cube or tear cake into bite size pieces and layer the bottom of a tall glass dish.
Pour prepared pudding (cooked or instant) over the cake.
Alternate layers of the fruit and top with Cool Whip.
Continue repeating the process to the top of bowl.
Last layer should end with Cool Whip and you can arrange some of the fruit on the top for eye appeal.
Can be used as a salad or dessert.
Serves 12.

title: plantation dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spoon filling evenly into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over filling.
Evenly distribute crushed pineapple over cake mix.
Slice butter into 1/2-inch pats and layer evenly over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over top.
Bake for 1 hour and check for doneness.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix and heat in a chafing dish.
This is also good served cold.
This makes a lot of dip, but may be cut down to family size using 1 package of cream cheese, 1 can of crabmeat and 1/3 of other ingredients.

title: indian squaw corn
directions: Cook bacon with microwave 3 minutes in an 8-inch glass cake dish.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain off excess fat.
Add corn and when it boils, stir in 1 slightly beaten egg and salt.
Mix thoroughly and let cook 3 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Recipe yields 4 servings.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Drain oranges, pineapple and cheese.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over fruit.
Stir well.
Fold in cottage cheese.
Lastly, fold in Cool Whip.
Let chill until very cold.
Use any Jell-O you like best.

title: coconut homestead cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place cookies in a greased pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Heat milk until skim forms.
Beat eggs and mix with sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add milk to egg mixture.
Pour into baking dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.

title: low-fat cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Chill, covered, 2 to 3 hours.
Use to dip fruit, pound cake cubes or pretzel logs.
Makes 2 cups.

title: zucchini turned pineapple
directions: Simmer for 20 minutes.
Let cool; pack into freezer boxes, leaving headspace, or simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack into hot pint jars.
Process in hot water bath for 30 minutes.

title: spanish chunk pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers overnight in cold water.
Put in stone jar. Make brine strong enough to float an egg (2 cups salt, 1 gallon water).
Let stand 3 days.
Soak in clear water for 3 days.
Then drain and cut in 1-inch pieces or smaller.
Mix 1/2 vinegar and 1/2 water and alum.
Let stand 3 days.
You know how much of this to make by measuring water drained off.

title: microwave peanut butter cereal bars
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil; grease foil.
In a 3-quart microwavable bowl, stir together sugar, Karo and peanut butter.
Cook on High 3 1/2 to 4 minutes, stirring twice, or until mixture is smooth and sugar is dissolved.
Add cereal.
Stir to coat well.
Press evenly into prepared pan.
Cut into squares. Store tightly covered.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage
directions: Parboil cabbage leaves in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Drain and trim out the thick center vein.
Combine ground meat, rice, parsley, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Roll tablespoonfuls in cabbage leaves and tie with white sewing thread.
Melt 2 tablespoons shortening in heavy skillet and brown cabbage rolls slightly on both sides.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake between 325° and 350° for 1 hour in unbaked pie shell.
"Delicious."

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Empty cottage cheese into a bowl and mix with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in mayonnaise by hand; then add the dill pickles.
Return to cottage cheese container and chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Put in zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Pour over other ingredients and bake at 400° or until knife comes out clean.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix butter and soup together.
Stir in beans and place onion rings on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk together.
Boil for 1 minute. Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add oatmeal and cocoa. Mix well.
Spoon onto buttered foil or wax paper.

title: easy pudding milkshake
directions: Pour milk into blender. Add pudding mix and ice cream. Blend at high speed 30 seconds or until smooth. Pour into glasses. Serve immediately. (Mixture thickens as it sits. Thin with additional milk, if desired.)

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Finely chop carrots and apples.
Mix all ingredients well. Makes 6 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: pennsylvania dutch salad with hot bacon dressing
directions: Chop bacon and fry until crisp.
Remove bacon and add to greens.
Add all other ingredients to beaten egg, except salad greens, and pour into the hot bacon fat.
Cook until thickened. Pour at once over the crisp, dry salad greens, such as lettuce, endive, dandelion or spinach.
A little chopped onion may be added, if desired.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks well, then add sugar. Gradually add whiskey to eggs, then add
this
to
dry ingredients
and
mix.
Fold in egg whites
which
have
been beaten.
Bake 1 hour in 300° oven in 2 loaf
pans (5 x 9-inch) which have been greased and lined with wax paper.

title: bread surprise
directions: *This recipe will make 2 loaves.
Bridgeford's frozen bread comes in packages of three.

title: oatmeal crunch bars(aka: peanut butter nightmares)
directions: Combine 2/3 cup peanut butter with remaining ingredients except chips in order given; mix well.
Press into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Add all three flavors; beat well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Add margarine and stir until melted. Add eggs and about half can of evaporated milk.
Stir in most of the cheese (save some for the topping). Put in casserole dish and add remaining evaporated milk, stirring gently. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° until it begins to bubble.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and water in a saucepan.
Bring slowly to 230° or until syrup spins thread.
Add peanuts and continue to cook to 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla, soda and salt. Stir until blended.
Pour into buttered or waxed paper covered pan (cookie sheet).
When cool, break into pieces.
Makes 1 to 1 1/2 pounds.

title: clam casserole
directions: Drain clams, add remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 2 qt. greased casserole.

title: marinated squash medley
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a jar. Cover tightly and shake well.
Pour dressing over squash. Toss gently. Cover and chill 4 hours.
To serve, toss again and serve with a slotted spoon. Yields 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and bananas.
Sift and add dry ingredients; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
If use Pyrex, bake at 25° lower.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts in microwave on High until tender and no longer pink (10 to 12 minutes).
Cut into cubes.
Cook broccoli in microwave until crisp.

title: meat loaf surprise
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, onion and green pepper. Shape into a loaf.
Bake in pan at 325° for 45 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes on the sides of the meat loaf.
Pour soy sauce over loaf.
Bake until vegetables are tender and meat loaf is brown on the inside.

title: fried noodles
directions: Fry green onions and garlic in one tablespoon olive oil for two minutes on medium-low heat.
Set aside.
Lightly brown pork in one tablespoon olive oil.
Lightly brown chicken in one tablespoon olive oil.
Add shrimp to garlic and onion.
Add soy sauce.
Add carrots, pork and chicken.
Cook noodles in microwave.
Add 1/2 cup water for each package noodles with seasonings.
Place noodles, seasonings and water in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes; stir.
Cook another minute.
Drain noodles.
Add to mixture and stir.
Serve.

title: salad
directions: Combine pineapple (juice and all) and sugar; bring to boil. Add Jell-O.
Let boil again.
Simmer for 2 or 3 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip blended together.

title: my favorite pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt.
Make a well and add salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Beat by hand.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Mix all together and bake as for custard pie.
Start at 10 minutes at 350°, then back to 325° until knife comes out clean, usually 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Put custard in baked pie shell; may be frozen.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape mixture into loaf.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Press green pepper rings and onion ring into meat loaf top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients well and pour into greased casserole. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake cookies
directions: Mix the cake mix, eggs and applesauce until well blended. Grease cookie sheet; spread mix.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Cool; spread frosting.
Cut into pieces.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and Cool Whip with electric mixer.

(Works best if cream cheese is softened.) Add about 1 teaspoon of jello to add the color and taste of strawberries or serve with fresh fruit slices, cherries, strawberries, peaches, apples, cantaloupe, etc.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add 2 egg yolks, milk and oleo.
Add the beaten egg whites last.
Pour into waffle iron.

title: grandma leisher's vegetable salad
directions: Mix corn, green beans, onions, pimento, celery and green pepper.
Bring all the remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over vegetables while hot.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and put in casserole.
Crush 1 tube of Ritz crackers; melt margarine.
Pour margarine into Ritz crackers.
Spread on top of casserole.
Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork mozzarella
directions: With a rolling pin, crush soup mix in pouch.
On wax paper combine soup mix, bread crumbs and black pepper.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and prunes.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with prune juice.
Add vanilla.
Lastly, add beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and margarine together, blending mixture very well.
Add sugar slowly.
Alternate eggs and flour, ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in Bundt pound cake pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Test for doneness. Let cool in pan for 20 minutes or so.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put soft shortening, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk in bowl.
Mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Add oatmeal and mix.
Lastly stir in chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in 375° oven. Watch closely to prevent burning.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs; add salt, vanilla, vinegar, coconut, raisins and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroon cupcakes
directions: Sift 1 cup sugar with flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat remaining 1/3 cup sugar in gradually.
Add flavoring.
Fold sifted dry ingredients into mixture.
Add about 2 tablespoons at a time. Gently fold in coconut.
Fill paper lined muffin pans about 2/3 full.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine water and sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil about 3 minutes, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and freeze. Serve slightly thawed.
(Sooooo good.
Kids will love it.)

title: wayne's waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg yolks, milk and oil; stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla extract, leaving a few fluffs.
Pour into hot waffle iron. Waffles are done when they are crisp on the outside.
Serve with warmed maple syrup.

title: brown rolls
directions: Mix sugar and 1/2 of milk or water.
Sprinkle yeast and let raise in warm place.
Cut up shortening in small pieces; add remainder of milk and put aside in warm place to melt butter.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Dissolve jello with two cups hot water. Add frozen strawberries. Let set awhile and then spread on cream cheese layer. Refrigerate until set. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until real light and fluffy.
Add well mashed bananas and beaten eggs.
Blend well.
Sift flour and mix in dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Bake in a well greased loaf pan for about 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Yield:
1 loaf or 4 mini loaves.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix well in order listed; refrigerate.

title: spaetzles
directions: You will need 2 or 3 large pots (1 with a lid), a large skillet, a
tea
kettle
of
hot
water,
a colander, a dinner plate, a
sharp
knife,
a
large
spoon
for
heavy mixing, a blender with
grating setting (or a hand grater), a large bowl and a large slotted spoon.

title: moist molasses crumb cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and take out 1 cup of crumbs for topping.
Mix water, corn syrup, molasses and baking soda and stir well.
Add liquid to remaining crumbs and stir.
Batter will be quite thin.
Spread crumbs over batter before baking.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when tested.

title: string bean casserole
directions: You take mayonnaise, peanut butter, eggs, flour, lettuce, tomatoes and mix it real good.
Then put it in the microwave and you make up the rest.

title: rolls or kuchen(small recipe)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water in first bowl.
Stir Crisco into 3/4 cup boiling water until melted in second bowl.
In third large bowl combine eggs, sugar, 1 cup warm water and salt. Add yeast mixture and Crisco mixture, then add 3 cups of flour one at a time.
Let rise 2 hours in warm place.
Make rolls or kuchen. Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and half of the milk.
Add beaten eggs.
Add rest of milk.
Fold in melted butter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and continue baking until knife comes out clean when inserted into center.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in 4 cups water with bay leaf, onion and celery until tender, about 2 hours.
Line a 9 x 12-inch pan (buttered) with crusted bread.
Layer boned chicken, 1 can mushrooms (drained) and 1 cup water chestnuts.
Dot with 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Lay Cheddar cheese over top.
Beat eggs and add to milk and salt.
Pour over cheese.
Mix 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can celery soup and pour over top.
Sprinkle diced pimento over top and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Let stand out 1/2 hour before baking at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top for last 1/2 hour.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Pour off 1 cup pickle juice and add sugar.
Put in saucepan and bring to boil, but do not boil.
Slice pickles and pack back in jar.
Pour juice and sugar mixture over sliced pickles.
Place in refrigerator for 10 days to 2 weeks.

title: classic golden buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening and butter until mixture is coarse and grainy.
Sprinkle buttermilk (or yogurt) over mixture and stir lightly with fork to blend.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead 8 to 10 times, until mixture is just rollable.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut into 2-inch biscuits with cookie cutter. Place on lightly greased baking sheets and brush tops with milk. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 5 minutes (it's easiest to put all ingredients in a bowl first, then only put half of mixture in the blender at a time).
After all is blended, stir in 1 1/2 cups of sugar, by hand.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls in hot water (or to taste).
Store in an airtight container until needed.

title: texas pie
directions: Melt
oleo
in	a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add pie filling and pineapple.	 Sprinkle
cake
mix	over
pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over that.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sauce for applesauce cake
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add and blend thoroughly the flour, sugar and water.
Cook until sauce thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add flavoring.
Pour over cake.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in pressure cooker for 15 minutes; drain.
Mash carrots and add sugar, margarine and cinnamon; mix well.
Add beaten eggs, 1 at a time; mix well and put in 8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch Pyrex dish.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook for 45 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut tips of chicken wings and discard.
Cut in half.
Brown in butter and garlic.
Add soy sauce; cover and simmer on low for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Tilt lid and continue simmering 1/2 hour more.
Add onion and mushrooms last 5 minutes.

title: potato-bacon-cheese soup
directions: Quick and easy.
Good hot or cold.
Follow the directions on the back of Knorr pasta sauces presto sauce mix.
Bows can be substituted for or with your favorite pasta.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook, drain and crumble sausage, let cool.
Spray pan with nonstick spray and place biscuits in pan.
Sprinkle with sausage. Whip eggs and milk together and pour on top, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
For a variety you can add onions, mushrooms and bell pepper.

title: strawberry icebox delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Beat until sugar has dissolved and then blend in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over graham cracker layer.
Layer strawberries over cream cheese layer and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix well and freeze in 9 x 12-inch container.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix and pour 1/2 in bowl (all but sour cream).
When thick put the carton of sour cream over it.
Cover with other 1/2 of mixture.

title: cracker macaroons
directions: Mix crackers, oats, coconut and salt.
Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Add flavoring.
Drop from teaspoon on greased and floured pan and bake 25 minutes in slow oven.
Lift from pan at once.
Yields 50 cookies.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in oil. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 pint.

title: icing for lazy daisy cake
directions: While the cake is baking, put the sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan and let melt slowly. Do not boil.
When the cake is done, take from oven and pour the icing mixed with the coconut over cake and replace in oven for a few minutes until icing settles and looks bubbly.

title: lemon-poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl; add vegetable oil and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer for 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour into a 10-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray.

title: first place chicken casserole
directions: Crush cornflakes and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Mix all ingredients except the cornflakes and margarine.
Place in buttered 9 x 12-inch dish.
Sprinkle with almonds and place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cornflakes and melted butter on top the last 15 to 20 minutes.

title: poppin john
directions: Cook all of above ingredients together until done, then add 1 1/2 cups Minute rice and cook until done.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Do not peel cucumbers.
Slice and add onions.
Add salt and cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly and let stand 3 hours. Drain thoroughly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients; add oil, eggs, water, pumpkin and nuts.
Fill three (1 pound) coffee cans 1/2 full.
Batter will rise to the top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-chicken-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling water until almost tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain and arrange in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread chicken on top.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: In a toaster, brown very lightly English muffins.
Place small amount of sauce on each muffin.
Spread.
Sprinkle cheese on each muffin.
Place in oven at 325° for ten minutes or until cheese has melted.
Serve hot.

title: buckeyes
directions: In large bowl mix Rice Krispies, margarine, confectioner sugar and peanut butter.
Refrigerate mixture.
Once mixture gets cold take out and make 1 inch balls.
Set on wax paper.
Melt chocolate morsels and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate with fork and place on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate. Makes 60 to 70 balls.

title: corn casserole
directions: You will need to butter the dish.

title: one, two, three, four cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks of well beaten eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Bake in greased and floured loaf or angel food cake pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes, then turn out on plate. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: quick and easy candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk and boil 4 minutes.
Stir in crumbs and peanut butter.
If it is too thin or looks too glossy, beat it a little and let cool a few minutes.
Then drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Remove stems from strawberries; rinse and drain. Puree strawberries in container of electric blender. Combine puree and sugar, stirring well. Set aside 10 minutes. Stir pectin into water. Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute. Pour pectin mixture into puree; stir 3 minutes. Ladle into sterilized jars, sealing at once with metal lids or ladle into frozen food containers and seal at once with plastic lids. Allow to stand at room temperature for 24 hours. Store in freezer. Yield: about 3 pints.

title: favorite noodle dish
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large pan, which has a tight cover and can be put in the oven, heat the oil.
Brown beef on all sides, a third at a time.
Remove beef to bowl as browned.

title: corn casserole iii
directions: Melt margarine; add all corn, sour cream, grated cheese and corn muffin mix.
Stir until well blended.
Place in an oblong baking dish, approximately 8 x 11-inches, that has been sprayed with a non-stick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix together the soups, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Add chicken; stir well.
Butter casserole dish and layer chicken mixture, chips and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Continue to layer with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine 1/2 pound lard, sugar and salt with boiling water. Set aside.
Combine yeast in medium bowl with cold water.
Set aside and allow to dissolve.
Beat 2 eggs and add to first mixture, then add yeast mixture.
Combine with flour.
Set in fridge at least 2 hours or overnight.
Roll out chilled dough on floured surface; spread with cinnamon and sugar mixture and raisins.
Roll and cut 3/4-inch slices.
Let stand covered one hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped chicken
directions: Wrap chicken with bacon and place in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread on top.
Bake 300° for 2 hours.

title: easy chicken noodle soup(microwave)
directions: Combine chicken pieces, carrots, onion, celery, 4 cups water, bouillon and parsley in 3-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid.

title: country ham clips
directions: Remove any fat from ham and cut into 1 1/2 in. strips.
Pour oil to depth of 3 inches in a Dutch oven.
Heat to 375° and fry ham strips until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichokes well.
Slice into quarters.
Add the mayonnaise and cheese (sliced in small pieces). Stir well.
Bake uncovered.
Serve with crackers while hot. Serves 10.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients except water.
Add water.
Stir quickly to mix.
Shape into balls and fry in deep fat.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: homemade condensed sweetened milk
directions: Blend in blender until smooth and thick.
Store in refrigerator until needed.
Makes 1 cup or the equivalent of 1 can of Eagle Brand.

title: super squash casserole(no one will ever know squash is in it)
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion (celery if

used). Drain. Combine with pimientos and water chestnuts. Put on bottom layer of casserole. Combine soup, sour cream and some of the water from the squash and onion. Spread over squash layer. Spread Cheddar cheese over soup layer. Melt margarine and combine with dressing mix. Spread over top. Bake at 325° until heated through, about 30 minutes. This recipe reheats great.

title: peach pie supreme
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, vanilla pudding, margarine, eggs and milk. Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate. Arrange drained peaches over batter in pie pan. Combine cream cheese, 10x confectioners sugar and peach juice. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon over peaches. Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then next 2 ingredients.
Mix well together.
Pour in greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter ale apple(all children of god will enjoy this one!)
directions: Spread each slice of apple with peanut butter.
Experiment with amounts of peanut butter.
Peanut butter also tastes good on bananas. May add wheat germ to taste.

title: dick's apple dumplings
directions: Cut each pie dough into 4 pieces (16) and wrap each piece around an apple half; place seam side down into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar, water, butter and vanilla; pour into the pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon over the dumplings.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and apples are tender.
Serve immediately.

title: beverly's lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and marshmallows in hot water.
Add juice from pineapple.
Chill until set.
Blend mayonnaise and cream cheese; add pineapple.
Beat well with gelatin mixture.
Add pecans and whipped cream.
Refrigerate until firm, overnight is best.
(Pecans may be omitted.)

title: mascarpone
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature and blend with sugar, egg yolks and liqueur.
Pour into small dessert cups. Chill. When served, top with a maraschino cherry.

title: meatballs and potatoes in a skillet
directions: Thoroughly mix ground beef, soft bread crumbs, 1 chopped onion, 1 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper and milk. Lightly shape meat mixture into 12 balls. Roll each ball in flour to coat well. In large, deep frying pan, melt shortening and brown the meatballs on all sides. Add sliced potatoes, sliced onions, boiling water, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Cover and cook over medium heat about 20 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender. May need to add a little more water. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper in butter in large pan. Add soup, corn, half and half and milk; stir well.
Then add all spices and crabmeat.
Cook until hot but not boiling, stirring frequently to avoid sticking.

title: claudine's rice pilaf
directions: *Add enough water so that with the chicken broth, the total liquid is 4 cups.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch to chocolate and water.
Boil about 3 minutes until thickened.
Take off heat, stir in butter and vanilla.
Enough to frost 2 layer cake.

title: manny's crisp bran cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Cream butter with sugars.
Mix in egg and vanilla until creamy.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Blend thoroughly.
Stir in coconut, pecans and bran flakes. Mixture will be stiff.
Drop by level tablespoons onto baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand on baking sheet 1 minute before removing.

title: susan's taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat; if you rinse meat with water, you can remove most of the fat.
Drain well on paper towels.
In a large bowl, add all ingredients except the dressing.
Toss well.
You can add the dressing to the salad before serving or have the dressing on the side.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolates
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Form into balls; dip in milk chocolate.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Heat shortening in a heavy, big pan.
Add meat, onion, celery and mushrooms; cook until meat is brown and crumbly.
Add tomatoes, catsup, chili powder, water, salt and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add flour and cook until mixture thickens.
Split warm hamburger buns and fill with mixture.

title: cookies for dogs
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Cut and place on oiled cookie sheet.
Cook at 250° for 3 hours.
Moisten or add extra corn meal or flour to make dough the proper consistency for cutting with cookie cutter.
We prefer gingerbread men, bird and cat cookie shapes.

title: green tomato preserves
directions: Combine tomatoes and sugar.
Bring to a boil and add cinnamon, mace, cloves and vinegar.
Cook for 1 hour just at boiling point. Ladle into sterilized jars; seal.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Clean and cut up broccoli and cauliflower in small pieces. Cut up green onions, small or big, whatever you want.
Fry bacon crisp and let lay on paper towel when done.
After cool, break up in little pieces and mix with cauliflower, broccoli and so on.

title: texas vegetable soup
directions: In a Dutch oven cook beef, onion and celery until beef is brown.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 10 minutes.
May be frozen. Makes 3 3/4 quarts.
This soup is quick to do and disappears.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add spices and cream.
Cook slowly until thick. Add Parmesan cheese.
Serve over cooked noodles.
May add ham slices to make a main dish.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths and make into balls.
Combine 1/2 tsp. cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar. Roll biscuit in cinnamon sugar and place in greased bundt or angel food cake pan.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and add 3/4 cup sugar and 3/4 tsp. cinnamon. Pour over biscuit balls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Prepare sauce and spaghetti as directed on package, but do not rinse spaghetti.
Add beaten eggs and Parmesan cheese to drained spaghetti.
Layer 1/2 of spaghetti in a 9-inch pie pan.
Lay 1/2 Mozzarella and extra Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve with spaghetti sauce poured over wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Add oleo to hot potatoes.
Combine with next 6 ingredients in blender or mixer.
Place mixture in greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows during last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: pound cake
directions: Have butter, eggs and whipping cream at room temperature. Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring.
Add flour alternately with whipping cream.
Grease and flour a tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or longer.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour; cool.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: slaw for freezer
directions: Chop cabbage and mix with salt.
Let stand 2 hours. Drain, if needed.
Add celery, pepper and onions.

title: vegetable and chicken hot dish
directions: Place cooked chicken in a greased casserole.
Boil vegetables 5 or 6 minutes.
Strain and set aside.
Heat cream of chicken and cream of celery soup (no water added) with Cheez Whiz until smooth.
Mix well with vegetables.
Pour over chicken and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle Durkee onions over top, the last 15 minutes.

title: chicken a la suisse(makes 6 servings)
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving:
Spread breasts flat; fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top.
Fold breasts over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks.
On waxed paper mix flour and paprika.
Coat chicken.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook chicken until browned on all sides.
Add wine and bouillon.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 30 minutes. Remove toothpicks.

title: chipmunk bars
directions: Combine water and dates, set aside to cool. Cream shortenings and sugar, add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Alternate dry ingredients with dates. Spread in a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and 1 c. chocolate bits.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Use on chicken or ribs. If meat is raw, cook for 2 hours.
If cooked, bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In 3-quart pot on medium-low heat, saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine until tender.
Add diced potatoes, the juice from the can of clams and just enough water to come within 1/2 an inch of the top of the potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble biscuits, add sugar, eggs, vanilla and enough milk to make cake-like batter.
Pour into greased pan and bake until brown on top or toothpick comes out almost clean.
Will be moist!
Can sprinkle with cinnamon for different taste.
Keep refrigerated.

title: batter(for fish, onion rings or zucchini strips)
directions: Mix and let stand 30 minutes, then add 1/4 teaspoon baking powder.
Dip and fry in hot oil.

title: hurry up tuna dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs. Place in greased casserole. Sprinkle top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: snowballs
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl; mix well. Add juice, blend well and chill. Shape into bite size balls. Roll in confectioners sugar and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving. Yield 40 balls.

title: warm meatball and lettuce salad
directions: Pinch off 1-inch pieces of ground beef to make approximately 32 free-form meatballs; cook in a heavy nonstick skillet over medium-high, shaking pan occasionally to brown, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Remove meatballs with slotted spoon; season with salt.
Add dressing to skillet; heat until hot. Meanwhile, combine lettuce, zucchini, tomato and red onion in a large bowl.
Add meatballs and heated dressing; toss lightly to coat evenly.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Serves 4.

title: baked chili spaghetti
directions: Cool spaghetti according to package directions.
Brown onion, pepper and seasoned meat in bacon drippings or oil.
Mix with tomatoes, mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, chili powder, salt, pepper and most of the cheese.
Add cooked spaghetti; mix well.
Place in remaining cheese, catsup and crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can be mixed beforehand and kept in refrigerator.

title: green chili lopez style
directions: On medium high heat, combine oil and pork shoulder and cook meat with bone until slightly toasted. Meanwhile, brown flour in separate pan. After flour is lightly browned, add 2-3 cups cold water and bring to boil, whisking together to remove any lumps (less water for thicker consistency, or more water for thinner consistency). Add pork, chilies, peeled tomatoes, salt and garlic to gravy mixture. Cover and simmer 20-30 minutes. Serve with rice and beans.

title: made rites(sloppy joe)
directions: Never use hamburger that has ever been frozen.
Bring to a boil water, ketchup and chili powder.
Boil for 10 minutes on low roll. Add onion and hamburger that you have broken apart and crumbled and added to water mixture.
Add other spices and stir often to break apart meat as much as possible.
Simmer 45 minutes and serve on rolls.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and let stand in cold water with salt added. After 10 minutes, remove chicken.
Wash and drain.
Remove skin from thighs. Dry with paper towel.
Put chicken in brown paper bag with flour. Close bag on top and shake until all chicken is coated with flour.

title: nothing to it cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 14-inch baking pan.
Spread the cherries and pineapple (undrained) in pan.
Sprinkle over that the cake mix (dry).
Drizzle over cake mix 1 1/2 sticks of butter, melted.
Add nuts over the top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break trimmings (bread croutons) into small pieces.
Toast and butter in oven.
Spread in 9 to 12-inch casserole dish.
Brown and drain sausage.
Sprinkle over croutons.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
You can substitute Spam, ham or crumbled bacon for sausage.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Combine cheese and butter in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, mixing gently.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion together.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350° in an uncovered baking dish.
A short time before the casserole is done, sprinkled crushed potato chips on top. Return to oven for at least 10 minutes.

title: fluffy chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare
whipped
topping
as directed on package.
Set aside 2 cups.
Mix 1 cup milk and chocolate mix with remaining whipped topping.
Beat
at	high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour in pie shell. (Add
nuts,
if
desired.)	Beat remaining whipped topping, 1/2 cup
milk,	vanilla
mix and peanut butter for 2 minutes on
high. Spoon on top of chocolate mixture.
Garnish with nuts if desired. Chill for several hours.

title: sherbet
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Freeze in hand cranked or electric ice cream freezer.
(Any flavor drink can be used.)

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and bake.
When cool, split layers.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese
stand at room temperature until soft.
Beat in condensed milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour filling into crust.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours. Top with pie filling.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the cup of water that is warm while preparing the dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients in a bowl. Then in another bowl mix the liquid ingredients.
Dump the dry ingredients into the liquid and stir; mix well.
Put aluminum foil over mixture and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
About 2 hours before serving, knead on pastry sheet.
Pinch 2 pieces and put in muffin pan, butter top and set aside until they rise. Makes 3 dozen.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Let chicken marinate in sauce 12 to 24 hours.

title: first rate chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar and a pinch of salt.
Add egg yolks and stir in milk.
Cook this mixture until thick in a double boiler.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes. Use the egg whites to make meringue.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Brown ground beef; drain. Add taco seasoning, corn and stewed tomatoes; mix well. Spray 13 X 9 inch pan. Put crushed tortilla chips on bottom of pan, then add meat mixture. Mix green onion dip and soup together. Spread on top of meat mixture. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Cover top of casserole with shredded cheese and bake for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese smooth and add sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and top with canned pie filling.
Chill in the refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: In saucepan, combine margarine and sugar.
Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Line a cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: baked bananas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 12 x 8 inch dish, melt butter in dish.
Add brown sugar, cinnamon and ginger.
Mix well.
Add bananas to butter mixture, mix gently to coat bananas.
Bake 10 minutes or until bananas are heated, basting with butter mixture. Serve over ice cream.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Butter bottom of pan or baking dish.
Pour into pan and top with cheese.
Heat oven to 325° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: squash patties(betty feezer recipe)
directions: Mix all together.
Batter will be thin like pancake batter. Pour into hot oil.

title: snappy glazed meat balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
In medium skillet, brown meatballs, turning occasionally.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally to coat meat balls with glaze.
Serve warm in chafing dish or electric frypan.
Makes 24 to 30 appetizers.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook noodles. Layer noodles, cottage cheese, Ragu and cheese. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese in sour cream.
Add extracts and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and mix well.
Lightly grease spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin trifle
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup of cake crumbs for top.
Divide remaining crumbs into four portions.
Sprinkle one portion into the bottom of trifle bowl.

title: nondairy mashed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes as for fries.
Sprinkle with Cajun spice.
Mix with egg white.
There will be too much egg white so she drained hers.
Spray Pam on cookie sheet.
Place potatoes on cookie sheet. Spray Pam on potatoes (small amount).
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Stir often.

title: creamy fruit sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine yogurt, coconut and extract; stir to combine.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: orange lemonade
directions: Place sugar in a saucepan.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups water.
Heat the mixture until the sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and allow mixture to cool to room temperature.
Squeeze juice from lemons and oranges (about 1 1/2 cups of each).
Add juices to cooled syrup. Pour over the mint leaves; cover and steep for 1 hour. Strain fruit syrup; pour into jars or place into a pitcher.
Cover and chill the fruit syrup.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: island cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 11 minutes.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix flour, meal, cheese and milk. Add pepper and onion just before you get ready to cook them.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place roast on large piece of foil.
Rub both sides with salt, m.s.g. and garlic powder.
Slice onion and dice (large pieces) the potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Layer onions and potatoes over roast and wrap securely in foil.
Place inside crock-pot on low before leaving in morning.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
May wrap carrots in separate piece of foil over meat package and combine when serving.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Mix with box of Rice Krispies.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: all eyes on the eggs
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Retain 2 Tbsp. bacon grease and add onion, green pepper, and mushrooms.
Cook until tender.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add apples and pecans.
Stir in dry ingredients; stir in vanilla and buttermilk.
Put in loaf pan.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon over batter.
Bake 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Add hot milk to bread, butter, and honey. Let stand until cold. Stir in eggs, cinnamon, vanilla, salt, and raisins. Pour into a greased 9 x 9 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Layer sliced potatoes and onions.
Between each layer, spread grated cheese, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Shake 2 cups milk with flour until smooth.
Pour over potatoes.
Add milk to about 1 inch below potato line.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Pat into the bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate bits.
Pour over top of other mixture and spread.
Cool in refrigerator 10 minutes and then cut.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up 4 slices of bread (any kind) and place in greased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Brown and drain sausage or bacon. Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage or bacon and bread.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour this over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be prepared the night before and refrigerated.

title: 3 layer surprise
directions: Put about 2-inches of cream potatoes in the bottom of casserole dish.
Slice wieners in bite-size chunks and put over top.
As many as you like.
Layer another 1 1/2 or 2-inches of potatoes.
Completely cover top of potatoes with shredded cheese and put in oven and bake until cheese is melted.
You can do this in microwave.

title: just like holly taters
directions: Scrub and cut potatoes in wedges. Combine all other ingredients in a plastic bag. Drop wedges in bag and shake. Place in single layer on flat cake pan. Dot with butter and bake until brown and tender, 400° for approximately 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Cook rice.
Beat eggs and combine with milk and rice.
Flake salmon and add with remaining ingredients.
Toss butter and crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger appetizer
directions: Mix all together.
Plump on Pepperidge Farm mini rolls, open-faced.
Bake at 250° for 1/2 hour.
Freezes well.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Skins may be removed. Mix remaining ingredients together in a shallow baking pan.
Roll chicken pieces in the mixture, then arrange in a single layer in the same pan. Bake at 375°, basting occasionally for 40 minutes (30 minutes if using boneless breasts).

title: golden oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a pie pan, combine crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, thyme and pepper.
In an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt butter with garlic powder.
Dip chicken pieces in garlic-butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish, skin side up.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 55 to 65 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Do not turn chicken pieces during baking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water and milk.
Add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan. Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in vanilla.
Pour immediately into baked pie shell.
Let cool at room temperature.

title: swedish dill-cured salmon(gravad lax)
directions: Combine all ingredients but fish.
Remove back and side bones of salmon.
Cut into 2 pieces lengthwise.
Rub inside of fish with spice mixture.
Place one side of salmon, skin side down and cover with dill.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and milk. Beat together.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pecan pies
directions: Layer 1/2 chocolate chips in pie shells, then layer pecans. Beat 4 eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Beat until well blended. Pour half over each pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, heat broth, salt and white pepper to a rolling boil (if broth is not heated to a rolling boil, eggs will not form threads!).
Stir green onion into eggs.
Pour egg mixture slowly into broth, stirring constantly with a fork, until egg forms threads.
3 servings.

title: company chicken
directions: Place dried beef in layer on bottom of casserole dish.
Wrap each half of chicken breast in a half strip of bacon.
Place on dried beef.
Combine soups and sour cream and pour over chicken. No seasoning needed.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serves 6 dinners. Serve with rice.

title: breakfast sausage
