directions: Brown sausage; drain. Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a pie plate. Let sit overnight or at least 1/2 hour before baking. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: mud flat pie
directions: Mix together
first
4 ingredients and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan for
the
crust.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° and then cool.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Blend all ingredients well in a food processor or blender. Garnish with a dollop of sour cream.

title: tropical scream
directions: Put desired juice in shaker container.
Select a sherbet and fill to 12 ounce line.
Place cap on container and shake vigorously.
Remove cap; pour in soda and stir.
Makes 2 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and spices.
Add nuts, candied fruit, raisins and mincemeat.
Mix until well coated with dry ingredients.

title: libby's pancake mixture
directions: Mixture should be slightly lumpy.
Drop large spoonfuls on hot griddle and cook both sides until brown.
Serve with hot syrup and more butter.
Should serve 3.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole, layer tortillas that have been cut in
strips.
Place layer of chicken that has been deboned and seasoned.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and onions and pour over chicken.
Top
with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
This recipe may be doubled for a
large crowd.
Make another layer of tortillas, chicken and end with sauce and cheese.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix milk and pineapple and add pie cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cool or freeze as desired.
Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs. Mix well. Add dry ingredients, then oats and nuts or raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: cinnamon apple brunch bake
directions: In saucepan, melt butter. Stir in brown sugar, apple pie filling, cinnamon and vanilla. Spread half of apple mixture in 2-quart shallow baking dish.

title: m-m-m-m good cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Press into greased spring-form pan.
Chill in freezer.

title: shrimp and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions together according to directions on package in a small amount of water.
Add soup, cheese, mushrooms and seasoning.
Mix well.
Add rice and shrimp.
Mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and melt oleo.
Mix together.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until it begins to bubble.

title: turnips au gratin
directions: Cook turnips in boiling salted water until almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cheese and stir to blend.
Stir sauce into cooked turnips and pour into buttered baking dish.
Mix crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake until golden in 10 x 6 x 2-inch casserole in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread out on tortillas.
Roll up. Chill for a few hours.
Slice and serve.

title: flubber(also called gak)
directions: In large bowl, mix glue, 3/4 cup hot water and food coloring. In another container (measuring cup), mix 2/3 cup hot water and Borax.
It
is important that glue doesn't get in the water and Borax mixture! Mix Borax and water mixture with glue in large bowl.
Knead with your hands until a solid blob!
This recipe can be doubled.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Saute onion in butter, then add all other ingredients and mix well.
(Save a little of the cheese for topping.)
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 10-inch greased pie plate. Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix peaches and dry Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese and sour cream.
Mix well; add Cool Whip.
Mix until well blended.
Add pecans and coconut, if desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: english toffee
directions: Place foil in a 9 x 15-inch jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with 1-inch hanging over edges, folding edges up to prevent dripping.

title: pantry plant food
directions: and the weary hours drag by.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in the butter over moderate heat for 10 minutes or until the shrimp are tender.
Add the mushrooms and cook for 5 more minutes.
Sprinkle in the flour, salt and pepper. Mix in well until it is smooth.
Stir in the sour cream and cook very gently for 10 minutes over low heat not allowing the mixture to boil.
Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Stir brown sugar into butter.
Drain beans and place beans into stacks of 10 beans each.
Wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around each stack of beans.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle the butter and brown sugar mixture on the bundles.
Bake at 350° until the bacon is crisp or until the sugar mixture sizzles.

title: sausage cheese muffins
directions: Brown sausage and drain well. Set aside. Mix together Bisquick, shredded cheese, Italian seasoning and red pepper. Stir in sausage. Mix soup with 1/2 can water and add to Bisquick mixture. Stir together until sticky dough forms. Spoon into well-greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 40 mini muffins.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine in mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.

title: teriyaki ribs
directions: In a bowl mix soy sauce, sugar, garlic and green onions.
In a pan add sesame oil and brown sesame seed, then add to soy sauce mixture.
Put meat in a dish and pour mixture over meat to marinate.
Put in refrigerator to marinate.
Marinate 6 to 8 hours. Bake in oven at 400°.
Cook for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix as directed.
Cook 1/2 batter in a 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Cook
at
350° for 15 minutes; let cool. Melt together the caramels, margarine and evaporated milk; let cool. Pour
sauce
over cool layer.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over sauce;
sprinkle
chopped
nuts over.
Pour second 1/2 of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until done.

title: spiced cran-apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients in 3 1/2 to 6-quart slow cooker. Cover and cook on low heat setting 4 to 6 hours. Remove allspice and cinnamon before serving. Makes 24 servings.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Cut cookie dough into 12 slices.
Cut each slice into quarters.
Arrange half the slices in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 1-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and cream cheese in mixer bowl until smooth.
Pour over cookie dough.
Top with remaining cookie dough, evenly spaced.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: pink fluff
directions: Mix together. Set in refrigerator over night.

title: brunch for a bunch
directions: After sausage is cooked and drained, grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Put in hash browns, salt and pepper, sausage, cheese, eggs and milk.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onions together, salt and pepper to taste.
In saucepan put 1 tbsp oil with 1 tbsp flour mix together then add can of enchilada sauce mix and simmer on low heat.
Fry tortillas in oil until soft. Dip in sauce put in 9x13 pan. Put meat in cheese on tortilla and roll up. After all the tortillas are rolled up, pour remaining sauce on top.
Top with grated cheese. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts. Serve with side dish of your choice.

title: country potato salad
directions: Don't peel the potatoes, please.
Wash the potatoes real good. When the potatoes get done, cut them into quarters.
Make the potato salad while it is hot.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients very well.
Good luck.

title: torte cake
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan; add flour and nuts. Bake at 350° until golden brown; let cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Gently combine ingredients and serve chilled.
Makes 8 servings; 3/4 cup each.

title: cranberry applesauce
directions: In saucepan, cook all ingredients except apple dip. Mash ingredients until smooth when cranberries and apples are cooked and candy slices melted. Add apple dip while still warm. Mix well.

title: banana holiday bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, dry ingredients and bananas. Add fruit and nuts. Put in
loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Glaze with corn syrup.

title: creamy hot chocolate
directions: Cook Stayman apples until they make a sauce.
Measure apples; add an equal measure of sugar.
Set oven at 350°.
Place apples and sugar in a deep roasting pan. Bake approximately 2 hours, stirring about every 20 minutes.
Before end of cooking time, add cinnamon to taste.
(May add allspice and cloves, if desired.) Mixture will sheet from spoon when done.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix eggs, shortening and buttermilk together, then add to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Store in tightly covered bowl in fridge.
Will keep 6 weeks.
When you want to bake some muffins, fill muffin pans with paper cups, then fill 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: beer batter for frying fish
directions: Mix together until thin.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Add beaten eggs to sugar, flour and seasonings.
Beat by hand until smooth.
Stir in rhubarb; mix well.
Pour into pie dish. Dot with butter or oleo and place vented top crust on top.
Bake 50 minutes at 400°.

title: noodle bake
directions: Brown meat, celery, onion and green pepper together.
Cook noodles until tender (drain).
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce to meat mixture, then add noodles.
Put into baking dish or roaster. Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
The longer and slower it is baked, the better the flavor.

title: onion and tomato yogurt
directions: Finely chop the onion and tomato.
Lightly beat the yogurt. Add the dried mint, fresh ground black pepper and salt.
Stir well to mix all the ingredients.
Chill slightly before serving.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix jello with boiling water well and chill until thick (semi-firm).
Prepare graham crust by mixing crumbs with 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Pat into pan.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, sugar and oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread evenly over cooled crust. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed and gelatin is slightly thickened.
Pour over cheese layer and refrigerate until set.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Melt butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Crush pretzels coarsely. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: barbecued muffin pizza cups
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce; simmer. Place biscuits in greased muffin tins; press to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 to 1/2 cup meat mixture into cup. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer each item in order, starting with lettuce.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar with 2 cups mayonnaise.
Spread on top of peas. Sprinkle top with 4 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: surprise chicken
directions: Place fryer breasts in baking dish which has been buttered. Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours or until tender.

title: potato soup 2
directions: Cook potatoes; cool, then peel.
Brown bacon until crisp; drain grease.
Slightly smash potatoes.
Add corn after drained. Add canned milk until soupy, then add butter.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together on medium heat for 10 minutes. Take off stove mix 1/2 c. sugar and 2 tsp. of self-rising flour. Put in unbake pie shell. Put lattice strips on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Cook onions and peppers in margarine until tender.
Cut chicken in small chunks.
Cube cheese and add to spaghetti while hot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Grease two 9-inch layer pans; dust each pan with 1/2 tsp. cocoa.
Set pans aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter blend and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.

Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating just enough to blend.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely, frost with Creamy Chocolate Frosting.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: "crustless" pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Gently pour over pecans.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus orange souffle
directions: Thoroughly mix gelatin, sugar and salt in saucepan. Beat egg yolks and 1 cup orange juice together.
Stir into gelatin mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture comes to boiling. Remove from heat.
Stir in orange and lemon peels and remaining juice.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Fold in whipped cream and spoon into molds.
Refrigerate until set, 2 to 4 hours.

title: sassy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake approximately 1 hour 5 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add red crushed pepper, clams, shrimp and clam juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add littlenecks.
Reduce heat and cook until littlenecks are opened.
Add parsley before serving.

title: little pizzas
directions: Brown meats together in large frying pan, breaking up meat into very small pieces.
Drain grease.
Cut up and add Velveeta.
Add oregano.
Mix thoroughly over very low heat until cheese melts. Spread mixture about 1/4 inch thick on party rye bread.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Can be frozen on cookie sheets and baked later for a little longer.

title: 10 bean soup
directions: Mix first nine ingredients together.
Cook for 2 1/2 hours. Add the green peppers, tomato paste and pasta.
Cook for another 1/2 hour.
Enjoy!!

title: chicken ala remae
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone. *(You can use canned chicken.) Chop up celery and onions, mix all ingredients. Put about 1 Tbsp. of mixture into the crepes. Roll and put in a pan. Cover crepes with Cream of Chicken Soup. Bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: danish puff
directions: Cut together butter and 1 c. flour like pie crust; add cold water.
Roll into ball.
Divide in half; spread on cookie sheet to size 4 X 12 (2 sections).

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut fryer as desired.
Mix catsup and Coke together.
Pour over chicken and bake until done, at 375°, for 1 hour.

title: waldorf salad
directions: *Is how much you want to put in.

title: ham-cheese quiche
directions: Butter 9-inch pie pan.
Take the ham and cut into small pieces.
Sprinkle over pie plate.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese.
Put eggs in blender; add milk.
Add Bisquick and beat for 1 minute. Place on top of ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 55 minutes.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Drain grapefruit; save liquid.
Place grapefruit sections into dish.
Pour pineapple (undrained) over grapefruit sections.
Mix gelatin and grapefruit juice together.
Heat sugar and water (do not boil!).
Pour over juice and gelatin.
Mix well and pour over grapefruit and pineapple.
Garnish with cherries.
Cool in refrigerator.
Tart and very good.

title: buttermilk praline
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cool over low heat to hard ball stage, about 45 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 3 to 4 cups pecans and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Candy will lose its sheen. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: apple torte
directions: Crust:
Combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and butter.
Mix and press 3/4 mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer for about 5 minutes. Baste ribs every 15 to 20 minutes. Serve rest with ribs.

title: oatmeal patties
directions: Mix; shape into patties and brown on both sides.
Place in casserole and pour over it one can mushroom soup diluted with 1/2 can water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: linguine and shrimp
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
In wok, heat dressing.
Add remaining 9 ingredients.
Cover, cook and stir 8 to 10 minutes. Add drained noodles and toss.

title: chicken mexican
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Spread in a greased casserole dish.
Cook 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: molly's chicken alfredo
directions: Place cutlets in casserole dish.
Place a slice of Mozzarella on each cutlet.
To prepare sauce, melt butter.
Add heavy cream, sour cream, grated cheese, some parsley and garlic powder.
Heat gently.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake at 350° until bubbly. Serve with spinach fettucine.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.
Bananas, pineapple, apples and orange slices go well with this dip.
Use fresh fruit.

title: crappie scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter, garlic and wine for 3 minutes.
Place crappie in pyrex dish or in individual au gratin dishes.
Pour butter sauce over each filet.
Sprinkle small amount of parsley flakes on top of each filet.
Bake 10-13 minutes, until flaky. Serve with hot garlic bread and use sauce for dipping. Serves 2.

title: power ranger cookies
directions: She cook's 'em with cookie recipe then she put some sugar on them. She has to spread peanut on the back.
Then she puts the Power Rangers on 'em.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Put macaroni in oven and cook for three days.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust: Mix together 1 to 1 1/2 sticks melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs; press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake slowly at 250° about 2 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and roll out on floured surface.
Cut and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until very light brown.
Remove and cool.

title: cheesy fish bake
directions: Cut fillets into 1-inch pieces.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together process cheese spread and milk.
Stir in peas, rice, dill weed and fish.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through, stirring once or twice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: enchiladas con pollo
directions: Heat oil in skillet and fry tortilla for a few seconds. Remove tortilla and dip in sauce. Set in baking dish and fill with about 1/4 c. filling. Roll and place with opening faced
down. When all the tortillas are filled, cover with remaining sauce. Bake at 350 until bubbly (about 20 min.). Top with additional cheese the last 10 min. Serve with sour cream if desired.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Boil sugar and Karo 1 minute.
Take from stove and add peanut butter.
I use extra chunky.
Stir and add to the corn flakes. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, oleo and oil. Add eggs. Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar and add to mixture. Add vanilla. Mix well and roll into balls. Flatten with fork dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: corn cheese quiche
directions: Use a 9-inch pie plate.
Melt butter and add all ingredients. Bake in microwave at 70% power (Medium) for 15 to 17 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then serve.

title: bundt danish orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream and oil in mixing bowl.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour in Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: decadent chocolate cookies
directions: Melt semi-sweet and bitter chocolate with butter over low heat until smooth.
Cool.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add chocolate and then flour mixture.
Beat until blended.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon amounts onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
With three kinds of chocolate, these are the ultimate in chocolate cookies.
This cookie has a soft-center and is moist and fudgy.
They will go fast!

title: green beans and sour cream
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Cook beans (whole or cut up).
Set aside.
Saute garlic in butter.
Add bread crumbs.
Cook until brown.
Add mixture and remaining ingredients to beans.
Place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place cut-up vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Place roast on top.
Sprinkle au jus powder over meat.
Add 2 cups water.
Can be cooked on high for about 4 hours or can cook on low all day while at work.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 7-Up, drained pineapple and bananas.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and let set in refrigerator until congealed.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Cook grits; add butter and cheese. Mix well. Add eggs, beaten, and milk.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake 45 minutes at 425°.
Delicious. Mickey's favorite.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a 4-quart ice cream freezer and finish filling with cold 2% milk.
(You may add fruit for a variety of flavors.)

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed, cool and crumble 1/2 cake into large glass bowl, such as punch bowl.
Mix pudding as directed, pouring 1/2 over cake.
Spoon 1 can pie filling over pudding.
Pour 1/2 drained pineapple over pie filling.
Spoon 1 container Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Repeat the process. Garnish with cherries on top layer.

title: easy italian cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in with cake mix.
Bake in 3 layers at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.
Let completely cool.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer #1:
Spread lettuce on bottom of a large bowl.

title: texas grits
directions: Stir grits into boiling water.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add salt and hot sauce, then stir in cheese and margarine.
Add eggs and pour into a greased baking dish. Bake, uncovered, in 300° oven for one hour.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach, onion and mushrooms together.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Combine soups and green chiles with tomatoes until smooth. Place a layer of chicken in greased deep casserole. Add a layer of tortillas, onion and cheese. Then top with layer of sauce. Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sharp cheese spread
directions: Add enough mayo to ingredients to make it spreadable.

title: french fried summer squash
directions: Combine eggs, milk and salt to make batter.
Dip squash in batter; roll in cornmeal.
Fry in deep fat until done.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate macaroon bars
directions: Beat cake mix, butter and 1 egg in large mixing bowl until mix is crumbly.
Firmly press mixture onto bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan.
Combine sweet condensed milk, 1 egg and vanilla in a medium bowl.
Stir in morsels, 1 cup coconut and pecans.
Spread over mixture in baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown (center will set when cooled).
Cut into bars.

title: mexican rice
directions: Fry rice in hot oil with chopped onion and garlic until lightly browned.
Drain off oil.
Add boiling broth, parsley, chili and salt.
Cover tightly and simmer for 25 minutes without lifting the lid.
Serve with main dish.

title: date nut cake
directions: Blend eggs, butter and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350°. Bake 35 minutes or until cake tester or toothpick comes out clean. When cake is cool, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Soften butter; mix with flour and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 1 cup whipped topping, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over cooked crust.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato.
Add vanilla and add enough confectioners sugar to make a ball.
Roll out.
Spread peanut butter on top.
Roll and chill.
Slice.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix well.
Pour into bottles and place in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.

title: jazzy nachos
directions: Cook hamburger with 1/2 taco seasoning until browned.
Mix in 1 can Hormel chili; simmer.
Lay out chips and spread hamburger and chili over top.
Add 1 layer of sour cream, lettuce and cheese.
Add toppings as desired.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine apples and sugar.
Gently fold in the bananas, carrots and nuts.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixing bowl.
Mix well to moisten dry ingredients.
Combine eggs and oil.
Stir into apple mixture.
Fill 18 greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup margarine, stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add cocoa mixture; beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and bake until melted.
In small saucepan, melt remaining 1/4 cup margarine; stir in 1/4 cup cocoa and remaining Eagle Brand.
Sti in powdered sugar and nuts.
Spread on warm cake.

title: sybil's punch
directions: Fix Kool-Aid as usual.
Mix in pineapple juice.

title: rachel's favorite pan-e-cakes
directions: Combine egg, milk (for thicker cakes, use 3/4 cup milk), oil and vanilla.
Add flour and dry ingredients; beat until smooth. Bake on a hot griddle with very little grease if using a teflon pan.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk until forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat it until it thickens.
Pour onto a buttered plate.
Let cool down.

title: magic puff tuna melts
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, mayonnaise and egg.
Add tuna, Cheddar cheese, celery, onion and lemon juice.
Spread mixture on muffins or buns, split apart.
Sprinkle a little cheese on top.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown, about 10 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill for 3 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together in bowl.
Melt butter.
Cut biscuits into 1/4's.
Dip biscuit pieces into butter, then roll in sugar mixture.
Place into baking dish (pie dish).
Bake until done.
Dump out on dish as soon as out of oven.
Pull apart and eat.

title: quiche
directions: Fill shell a little more than half full with alternating layers of cheese and ham.
Refrigerate.
Beat together the eggs, cream and salt.
Refrigerate separately.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw bread in microwave 10 minutes on Defrost setting.
Cut bread in large chunks.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan (buttered).
Melt butter; add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add pudding mix and milk; mix all together.
Pour over bread chunks.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Dump out on aluminum foil.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture, alternating with milk.
Add berries and vanilla. Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: skillet frittata
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Add potatoes and chopped veggies; cook 5 minutes or until potatoes are browned, stirring occasionally. Beat egg, milk and salt until well blended. Pour evenly over potato mixture; cover, reduce heat to medium-low and cook 10 to 12 minutes or until center is set. Sprinkle with shredded cheese; cover and let stand 5 to 6 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: cherry cream puff
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to boiling in 1-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Drop dough by tablespoon onto greased baking sheet, forming an 8-inch ring.
Smooth with spatula.
Bake until puffed and golden brown, 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool ring.
Cut top with sharp knife.
Pull out any soft dough.
Beat milk, sour cream, pudding and pie filling (dry) and extract in small mixing bowl until blended (low speed).
Fill cream puff ring with pudding mixture.
Spoon 1/2 can cherry pie filling onto pudding mixture. Replace top of cream puff.
Spoon remaining cherry pie filling on top.
Refrigerate.

title: marinated macaroni salad
directions: Cook shells according to directions.
Rinse in cold water. Drain and set aside.
Chop green pepper, onion and celery into small pieces.
Grate carrot.
Mix soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, dry mustard, pepper and salt in saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over macaroni.
Add vegetables.
Marinate overnight or for several hours.

title: company chicken dish
directions: Put chipped beef on bottom of baking dish.
Wrap each chicken breast in 1 slice of bacon.
Put on top of chipped beef.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.

title: hot ham and cheese buns
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on buns.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in oven or on cookie sheet, covered.

title: sweet-sour sausage balls
directions: Mix together the sausage, eggs and bread crumbs.
Using palms of hands, shape mixture into balls the size of small walnuts. Saute in frying pan until browned on all sides; drain.
Combine ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce; pour over sausage balls and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve hot. Yields 150 appetizers.

title: walnut crescents
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended. Cover and chill 30 minutes or until firm enough to handle.
Break off small piece of dough and on lightly floured surface, roll into finger-thick strips.
Cut in 2-inch lengths.
Taper ends, shape in crescents.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 300° oven 18 to 20 minutes or until firm to the touch. While warm, roll in granulated sugar.
Cool on rack.
Store in airtight container in cool place.

title: fresh corn bread
directions: Cut corn from cob, scraping cob to remove the pulp.
Combine corn, eggs, milk, bacon drippings, sugar, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Gradually stir in flour.
Heat a well-greased 8-inch cast-iron skillet in a 400° oven for 3 minutes or until very hot. Pour batter into hot skillet and bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Bake a yellow cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix in saucepan, flour and milk.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool.
In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, Crisco, vanilla, salt and margarine.
Beat with mixer until fluffy.
Add cooled milk mixture.
Beat until fluffy.
Cut cooled cake, layerwise. Put all filling between two layers.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Melt margarine and pour into mixture. Pour peaches in bottom of pan and top with mixture.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft.
Add flour to mixture. Add milk, stirring constantly. Add egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Put crabmeat in a bowl and pour sauce over it.
Blend well and place in a lightly greased casserole and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° until browned.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add shredded cabbage.
Cook over low heat for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt and paprika and simmer until cabbage is just tender.
Combine cream and vinegar and add to cabbage and stir gently.
Serve hot.

title: beef pinwheels
directions: Mix beef
and dry onion soup mix. Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients to make dough.
Roll out to 10 x 12-inches. Spread meat on top and roll up. Chill 1 hour and slice 3/4-inch thick. Place pinwheels on baking sheet and bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
May serve with mushroom sauce or a tomato sauce. Makes about 20.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Blend together the lemonade, which has been softened but not thawed, and the milk.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Add the food coloring, enough to make a pretty pink color.
Put into the crusts and chill at least 3 hours.

title: microwave summer squash toss
directions: Cut squash and zucchini into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in glass casserole dish.
Add pimentos, water, salt, pepper, basil and garlic powder.
Dot with butter.
Cover dish.
Cook in microwave on High for 9 to 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Let stand covered for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in
large
bowl and mix well. Pour into lightly greased
x
x 3/4-inch baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler supreme
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cinnamon in a Dutch oven; set aside until syrup forms.
Bring peach mixture to a boil; reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat; add almond extract and butter, stirring until butter melts.

title: spicy fish(fat free)
directions: Place water and margarine in skillet.
Heat until boils.
Add fish.
Cook on medium heat until fish flakes with a fork. Sprinkle seasoning on fish.
Cover.
Simmer 5 more minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Tear lettuce and cauliflower into bite size pieces; toss with bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese, sugar and onion together.
Pour over lettuce mixture.

title: homecoming potato salad
directions: Mix together cooled potatoes, eggs, onions, salad cubes, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add mustard and enough mayonnaise to mix all ingredients well.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Heat all ingredients until blended. Pour over carrots. Dish is ready to serve.

title: our favorite stew
directions: Bake in small covered roaster at 250° or in crock-pot at medium for 5 or 6 hours.
Very good.

title: refrigerator roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in potatoes, sugar, shortening, eggs, salt and 3 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up. Cover bowl tightly.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours, but no longer than 5 days.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine ingredients and cook 2 minutes after mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Cool and frost.
